  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'These are the words of Jeremiah son of Hilkiah, one of the priests
        from the town of Anathoth in the land of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> first gave messages to Jeremiah during
        the thirteenth year of the reign of Josiah son of Amon, king of Judah.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: "The thirteenth year of Josiah\u2019s reign was 627 "
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s messages continued throughout
        the reign of King Jehoiakim, Josiah\u2019s son, until the eleventh year of
        the reign of King Zedekiah, another of Josiah\u2019s sons. In August[COMMENT[0]]
        of that eleventh year the people of Jerusalem were taken away as captives.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'In the fifth month, '
        - ft: "of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar. A number of events in Jeremiah
            can be cross-checked with dates in surviving Babylonian records and related
            accurately to our modern calendar. The fifth month in the eleventh year
            of Zedekiah\u2019s reign occurred within the months of August and September
            586 "
          body: 
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Call and First Visions"
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me this message:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI knew you before I formed you in your mother\u2019s womb.\n\tBefore
        you were born I set you apart\n\tand appointed you as my prophet to the nations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\u201D I said,
        \u201CI can\u2019t speak for you! I\u2019m too young!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replied, \u201CDon\u2019t say, \u2018I\u2019m
        too young,\u2019 for you must go wherever I send you and say whatever I tell
        you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And don\u2019t be afraid of the people, for I will be with you and
        will protect you. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reached out and touched my mouth
        and said,\n\t\u201CLook, I have put my words in your mouth!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Today I appoint you to stand up\n\tagainst nations and kingdoms.\n\tSome
        you must uproot and tear down,\n\tdestroy and overthrow.\n\tOthers you must
        build up\n\tand plant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CLook, Jeremiah!
        What do you see?\u201D\n\tAnd I replied, \u201CI see a branch from an almond
        tree.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CThat\u2019s right,
        and it means that I am watching,[COMMENT[0]] and I will certainly carry out
        all my plans.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: "The Hebrew word for \u201Cwatching\u201D "
          body: '(shoqed) '
        - ft: "sounds like the word for \u201Calmond tree\u201D "
          body: (shaqed).
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to me again and asked,
        \u201CWhat do you see now?\u201D\n\tAnd I replied, \u201CI see a pot of boiling
        water, spilling from the north.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYes,\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201Cfor
        terror from the north will boil out on the people of this land. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen! I am calling the armies of the kingdoms of the north to come
        to Jerusalem. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\n\t\u201CThey
        will set their thrones\n\tat the gates of the city.\n\tThey will attack its
        walls\n\tand all the other towns of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will pronounce judgment\n\ton my people for all their evil\u2014\n\tfor
        deserting me and burning incense to other gods.\n\tYes, they worship idols
        made with their own hands!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGet up and prepare for action.\n\tGo out and tell them everything
        I tell you to say.\n\tDo not be afraid of them,\n\tor I will make you look
        foolish in front of them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For see, today I have made you strong\n\tlike a fortified city that
        cannot be captured,\n\tlike an iron pillar or a bronze wall.\n\tYou will
        stand against the whole land\u2014\n\tthe kings, officials, priests, and
        people of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will fight you, but they will fail.\n\tFor I am with you, and
        I will take care of you.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have
        spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Case against His People"
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me another message. He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo and shout this message to Jerusalem. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\n\t\u201CI remember how eager you were to please me\n\tas a young bride
        long ago,\n\thow you loved me and followed me\n\teven through the barren
        wilderness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In those days Israel was holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tthe
        first of his children.[COMMENT[0]]All who harmed his people were declared
        guilty,\n\tand disaster fell on them.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the firstfruits of his harvest.
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, people
        of Jacob\u2014all you families of Israel! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CWhat
        did your ancestors find wrong with me\n\tthat led them to stray so far from
        me?\n\tThey worshiped worthless idols,\n\tonly to become worthless themselves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They did not ask, \u2018Where is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\twho
        brought us safely out of Egypt\n\tand led us through the barren wilderness\u2014\n\ta
        land of deserts and pits,\n\ta land of drought and death,\n\twhere no one
        lives or even travels?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd when I brought you into a fruitful land\n\tto enjoy its
        bounty and goodness,\n\tyou defiled my land\n\tand corrupted the possession
        I had promised you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The priests did not ask,\n\t\u2018Where is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?\u2019\n\tThose
        who taught my word ignored me,\n\tthe rulers turned against me,\n\tand the
        prophets spoke in the name of Baal,\n\twasting their time on worthless idols.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, I will bring my case against you,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CI
        will even bring charges against your children\u2019s children\n\tin the years
        to come.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo west and look in the land of Cyprus[COMMENT[0]];\n\tgo east
        and search through the land of Kedar.\n\tHas anyone ever heard of anything\n\tas
        strange as this?  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Kittim.
    - title: 
      content: "Has any nation ever traded its gods for new ones,\n\teven though
        they are not gods at all?\n\tYet my people have exchanged their glorious
        God[COMMENT[0]]for worthless idols!  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: their glory.
    - title: 
      content: "The heavens are shocked at such a thing\n\tand shrink back in horror
        and dismay,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor my people have done two evil things:\n\tThey have abandoned
        me\u2014\n\tthe fountain of living water.\n\tAnd they have dug for themselves
        cracked cisterns\n\tthat can hold no water at all!  "
      comments: []
    - title: "The Results of Israel\u2019s Sin"
      content: "\u201CWhy has Israel become a slave?\n\tWhy has he been carried away
        as plunder?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Strong lions have roared against him,\n\tand the land has been destroyed.\n\tThe
        towns are now in ruins,\n\tand no one lives in them anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Egyptians, marching from their cities of Memphis[COMMENT[0]] and
        Tahpanhes,\n\thave destroyed Israel\u2019s glory and power.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Noph.
    - title: 
      content: "And you have brought this upon yourselves\n\tby rebelling against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,\n\teven though he was leading you
        on the way!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat have you gained by your alliances with Egypt\n\tand your
        covenants with Assyria?\n\tWhat good to you are the streams of the Nile[COMMENT[0]]or
        the waters of the Euphrates River?[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:18a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'of Shihor, '
        - ft: a branch of the Nile River.
          body: 
      - number: '2:18b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the river?
    - title: 
      content: "Your wickedness will bring its own punishment.\n\tYour turning from
        me will shame you.\n\tYou will see what an evil, bitter thing it is\n\tto
        abandon the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and not to fear him.\n\tI,
        the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLong ago I broke the yoke that oppressed you\n\tand tore away
        the chains of your slavery,\n\tbut still you said,\n\t\u2018I will not serve
        you.\u2019\n\tOn every hill and under every green tree,\n\tyou have prostituted
        yourselves by bowing down to idols.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I was the one who planted you,\n\tchoosing a vine of the purest
        stock\u2014the very best.\n\tHow did you grow into this corrupt wild vine?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No amount of soap or lye can make you clean.\n\tI still see the stain
        of your guilt.\n\tI, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have
        spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: Israel, an Unfaithful Wife
      content: "\u201CYou say, \u2018That\u2019s not true!\n\tI haven\u2019t worshiped
        the images of Baal!\u2019\n\tBut how can you say that?\n\tGo and look in
        any valley in the land!\n\tFace the awful sins you have done.\n\tYou are
        like a restless female camel\n\tdesperately searching for a mate.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You are like a wild donkey,\n\tsniffing the wind at mating time.\n\tWho
        can restrain her lust?\n\tThose who desire her don\u2019t need to search,\n\tfor
        she goes running to them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When will you stop running?\n\tWhen will you stop panting after other
        gods?\n\tBut you say, \u2018Save your breath.\n\tI\u2019m in love with these
        foreign gods,\n\tand I can\u2019t stop loving them now!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIsrael is like a thief\n\twho feels shame only when he gets
        caught.\n\tThey, their kings, officials, priests, and prophets\u2014\n\tall
        are alike in this.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "To an image carved from a piece of wood they say,\n\t\u2018You are
        my father.\u2019\n\tTo an idol chiseled from a block of stone they say,\n\t\u2018You
        are my mother.\u2019\n\tThey turn their backs on me,\n\tbut in times of trouble
        they cry out to me,\n\t\u2018Come and save us!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But why not call on these gods you have made?\n\tWhen trouble comes,
        let them save you if they can!\n\tFor you have as many gods\n\tas there are
        towns in Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why do you accuse me of doing wrong?\n\tYou are the ones who have
        rebelled,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have punished your children,\n\tbut they did not respond
        to my discipline.\n\tYou yourselves have killed your prophets\n\tas a lion
        kills its prey.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO my people, listen to the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\n\tHave
        I been like a desert to Israel?\n\tHave I been to them a land of darkness?\n\tWhy
        then do my people say, \u2018At last we are free from God!\n\tWe don\u2019t
        need him anymore!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does a young woman forget her jewelry,\n\tor a bride her wedding
        dress?\n\tYet for years on end\n\tmy people have forgotten me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow you plot and scheme to win your lovers.\n\tEven an experienced
        prostitute could learn from you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your clothing is stained with the blood of the innocent and the poor,\n\tthough
        you didn\u2019t catch them breaking into your houses!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And yet you say,\n\t\u2018I have done nothing wrong.\n\tSurely God
        isn\u2019t angry with me!\u2019\n\tBut now I will punish you severely\n\tbecause
        you claim you have not sinned.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "First here, then there\u2014\n\tyou flit from one ally to another
        asking for help.\n\tBut your new friends in Egypt will let you down,\n\tjust
        as Assyria did before.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In despair, you will be led into exile\n\twith your hands on your
        heads,\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected the nations you
        trust.\n\tThey will not help you at all."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf a man divorces a woman\n\tand she goes and marries someone
        else,\n\the will not take her back again,\n\tfor that would surely corrupt
        the land.\n\tBut you have prostituted yourself with many lovers,\n\tso why
        are you trying to come back to me?\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook at the shrines on every hilltop.\n\tIs there any place
        you have not been defiled\n\tby your adultery with other gods?\n\tYou sit
        like a prostitute beside the road waiting for a customer.\n\tYou sit alone
        like a nomad in the desert.\n\tYou have polluted the land with your prostitution\n\tand
        your wickedness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That\u2019s why even the spring rains have failed.\n\tFor you are
        a brazen prostitute and completely shameless.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet you say to me,\n\t\u2018Father, you have been my guide since
        my youth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Surely you won\u2019t be angry forever!\n\tSurely you can forget
        about it!\u2019\n\tSo you talk,\n\tbut you keep on doing all the evil you
        can.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Judah Follows Israel\u2019s Example"
      content: "During the reign of King Josiah, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to me, \u201CHave you seen what fickle Israel has done? Like a wife
        who commits adultery, Israel has worshiped other gods on every hill and under
        every green tree. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I thought, \u2018After she has done all this, she will return to
        me.\u2019 But she did not return, and her faithless sister Judah saw this. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She saw[COMMENT[0]] that I divorced faithless Israel because of her
        adultery. But that treacherous sister Judah had no fear, and now she, too,
        has left me and given herself to prostitution. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls, one Greek manuscript, and Syriac version;
            Masoretic Text reads '
          body: I saw.
    - title: 
      content: "Israel treated it all so lightly\u2014she thought nothing of committing
        adultery by worshiping idols made of wood and stone. So now the land has
        been polluted. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But despite all this, her faithless sister Judah has never sincerely
        returned to me. She has only pretended to be sorry. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Hope for Wayward Israel
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CEven faithless
        Israel is less guilty than treacherous Judah! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, go and give this message to Israel.[COMMENT[0]] This is
        what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CO Israel, my faithless
        people,\n\tcome home to me again,\n\tfor I am merciful.\n\tI will not be
        angry with you forever.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: toward the north.
    - title: 
      content: "Only acknowledge your guilt.\n\tAdmit that you rebelled against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God\n\tand committed adultery against him\n\tby
        worshiping idols under every green tree.\n\tConfess that you refused to listen
        to my voice.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CReturn home, you wayward children,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cfor
        I am your master.\n\tI will bring you back to the land of Israel[COMMENT[0]]\u2014\n\tone
        from this town and two from that family\u2014\n\tfrom wherever you are scattered.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "And I will give you shepherds after my own heart,\n\twho will guide
        you with knowledge and understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd when your land is once more filled with people,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, \u201Cyou will no longer wish for \u2018the
        good old days\u2019 when you possessed the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Covenant. You will not miss those days or even remember them, and there will
        be no need to rebuild the Ark. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day Jerusalem will be known as \u2018The Throne of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u2019
        All nations will come there to honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        They will no longer stubbornly follow their own evil desires. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In those days the people of Judah and Israel will return together
        from exile in the north. They will return to the land I gave your ancestors
        as an inheritance forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI thought to myself,\n\t\u2018I would love to treat you as
        my own children!\u2019\n\tI wanted nothing more than to give you this beautiful
        land\u2014\n\tthe finest possession in the world.\n\tI looked forward to
        your calling me \u2018Father,\u2019\n\tand I wanted you never to turn from
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you have been unfaithful to me, you people of Israel!\n\tYou
        have been like a faithless wife who leaves her husband.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Voices are heard high on the windswept mountains,\n\tthe weeping
        and pleading of Israel\u2019s people.\n\tFor they have chosen crooked paths\n\tand
        have forgotten the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy wayward children,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Ccome
        back to me, and I will heal your wayward hearts.\u201D\n\t\u201CYes, we\u2019re
        coming,\u201D the people reply,\n\t\u201Cfor you are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our worship of idols on the hills\n\tand our religious orgies on
        the mountains\n\tare a delusion.\n\tOnly in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God\n\twill Israel ever find salvation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From childhood we have watched\n\tas everything our ancestors worked
        for\u2014\n\ttheir flocks and herds, their sons and daughters\u2014\n\twas
        squandered on a delusion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let us now lie down in shame\n\tand cover ourselves with dishonor,\n\tfor
        we and our ancestors have sinned\n\tagainst the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God.\n\tFrom our childhood to this day\n\twe have never obeyed him.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO Israel,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cif
        you wanted to return to me, you could.\n\tYou could throw away your detestable
        idols\n\tand stray away no more.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then when you swear by my name, saying,\n\t\u2018As surely as the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives,\u2019\n\tyou could do so\n\twith truth,
        justice, and righteousness.\n\tThen you would be a blessing to the nations
        of the world,\n\tand all people would come and praise my name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Coming Judgment against Judah
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to the people of
        Judah and Jerusalem:\n\t\u201CPlow up the hard ground of your hearts!\n\tDo
        not waste your good seed among thorns.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O people of Judah and Jerusalem,\n\tsurrender your pride and power.\n\tChange
        your hearts before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,[COMMENT[0]]or my
        anger will burn like an unquenchable fire\n\tbecause of all your sins.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Circumcise yourselves to the '
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CShout to Judah, and broadcast to Jerusalem!\n\tTell them to
        sound the alarm throughout the land:\n\t\u2018Run for your lives!\n\tFlee
        to the fortified cities!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Raise a signal flag as a warning for Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]]:\n\t\u2018Flee
        now! Do not delay!\u2019\n\tFor I am bringing terrible destruction upon you\n\tfrom
        the north.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "A lion stalks from its den,\n\ta destroyer of nations.\n\tIt has
        left its lair and is headed your way.\n\tIt\u2019s going to devastate your
        land!\n\tYour towns will lie in ruins,\n\twith no one living in them anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So put on clothes of mourning\n\tand weep with broken hearts,\n\tfor
        the fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tis still upon us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cthe
        king and the officials will tremble in fear.\n\tThe priests will be struck
        with horror,\n\tand the prophets will be appalled.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tthe
        people have been deceived by what you said,\n\tfor you promised peace for
        Jerusalem.\n\tBut the sword is held at their throats!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The time is coming when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will say\n\tto
        the people of Jerusalem,\n\t\u201CMy dear people, a burning wind is blowing
        in from the desert,\n\tand it\u2019s not a gentle breeze useful for winnowing
        grain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is a roaring blast sent by me!\n\tNow I will pronounce your destruction!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our enemy rushes down on us like storm clouds!\n\tHis chariots are
        like whirlwinds.\n\tHis horses are swifter than eagles.\n\tHow terrible it
        will be, for we are doomed!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O Jerusalem, cleanse your heart\n\tthat you may be saved.\n\tHow
        long will you harbor\n\tyour evil thoughts?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your destruction has been announced\n\tfrom Dan and the hill country
        of Ephraim.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWarn the surrounding nations\n\tand announce this to Jerusalem:\n\tThe
        enemy is coming from a distant land,\n\traising a battle cry against the
        towns of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They surround Jerusalem like watchmen around a field,\n\tfor my people
        have rebelled against me,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYour own actions have brought this upon you.\n\tThis punishment
        is bitter, piercing you to the heart!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jeremiah Weeps for His People
      content: "My heart, my heart\u2014I writhe in pain!\n\tMy heart pounds within
        me! I cannot be still.\n\tFor I have heard the blast of enemy trumpets\n\tand
        the roar of their battle cries.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Waves of destruction roll over the land,\n\tuntil it lies in complete
        desolation.\n\tSuddenly my tents are destroyed;\n\tin a moment my shelters
        are crushed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How long must I see the battle flags\n\tand hear the trumpets of
        war?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy people are foolish\n\tand do not know me,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CThey are stupid children\n\twho
        have no understanding.\n\tThey are clever enough at doing wrong,\n\tbut they
        have no idea how to do right!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Vision of Coming Disaster"
      content: "I looked at the earth, and it was empty and formless.\n\tI looked
        at the heavens, and there was no light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I looked at the mountains and hills,\n\tand they trembled and shook.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I looked, and all the people were gone.\n\tAll the birds of the sky
        had flown away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I looked, and the fertile fields had become a wilderness.\n\tThe
        towns lay in ruins,\n\tcrushed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        fierce anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe whole
        land will be ruined,\n\tbut I will not destroy it completely.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth will mourn\n\tand the heavens will be draped in black\n\tbecause
        of my decree against my people.\n\tI have made up my mind and will not change
        it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At the noise of charioteers and archers,\n\tthe people flee in terror.\n\tThey
        hide in the bushes\n\tand run for the mountains.\n\tAll the towns have been
        abandoned\u2014\n\tnot a person remains!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What are you doing,\n\tyou who have been plundered?\n\tWhy do you
        dress up in beautiful clothing\n\tand put on gold jewelry?\n\tWhy do you
        brighten your eyes with mascara?\n\tYour primping will do you no good!\n\tThe
        allies who were your lovers\n\tdespise you and seek to kill you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I hear a cry, like that of a woman in labor,\n\tthe groans of a woman
        giving birth to her first child.\n\tIt is beautiful Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]]gasping
        for breath and crying out,\n\t\u201CHelp! I\u2019m being murdered!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '4:31 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the daughter of Zion.
  - verses:
    - title: The Sins of Judah
      content: "\u201CRun up and down every street in Jerusalem,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CLook
        high and low; search throughout the city!\n\tIf you can find even one just
        and honest person,\n\tI will not destroy the city.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But even when they are under oath,\n\tsaying, \u2018As surely as
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives,\u2019\n\tthey are still telling lies!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you are searching for honesty.\n\tYou
        struck your people,\n\tbut they paid no attention.\n\tYou crushed them,\n\tbut
        they refused to be corrected.\n\tThey are determined, with faces set like
        stone;\n\tthey have refused to repent.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CBut what can we expect from the poor?\n\tThey
        are ignorant.\n\tThey don\u2019t know the ways of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tThey
        don\u2019t understand God\u2019s laws.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will go and speak to their leaders.\n\tSurely they know the
        ways of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand understand God\u2019s laws.\u201D\n\tBut
        the leaders, too, as one man,\n\thad thrown off God\u2019s yoke\n\tand broken
        his chains.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now a lion from the forest will attack them;\n\ta wolf from the
        desert will pounce on them.\n\tA leopard will lurk near their towns,\n\ttearing
        apart any who dare to venture out.\n\tFor their rebellion is great,\n\tand
        their sins are many.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow can I pardon you?\n\tFor even your children have turned
        from me.\n\tThey have sworn by gods that are not gods at all!\n\tI fed my
        people until they were full.\n\tBut they thanked me by committing adultery\n\tand
        lining up at the brothels.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are well-fed, lusty stallions,\n\teach neighing for his neighbor\u2019s
        wife.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Should I not punish them for this?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CShould
        I not avenge myself against such a nation?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo down the rows of the vineyards and destroy the grapevines,\n\tleaving
        a scattered few alive.\n\tStrip the branches from the vines,\n\tfor these
        people do not belong to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Israel and Judah\n\tare full of treachery against me,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey have lied about the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand
        said, \u2018He won\u2019t bother us!\n\tNo disasters will come upon us.\n\tThere
        will be no war or famine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God\u2019s prophets are all windbags\n\twho don\u2019t really speak
        for him.\n\tLet their predictions of disaster fall on themselves!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says:\n\t\u201CBecause the people are talking like this,\n\tmy messages
        will flame out of your mouth\n\tand burn the people like kindling wood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O Israel, I will bring a distant nation against you,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CIt is a mighty nation,\n\tan
        ancient nation,\n\ta people whose language you do not know,\n\twhose speech
        you cannot understand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their weapons are deadly;\n\ttheir warriors are mighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will devour the food of your harvest;\n\tthey will devour your
        sons and daughters.\n\tThey will devour your flocks and herds;\n\tthey will
        devour your grapes and figs.\n\tAnd they will destroy your fortified towns,\n\twhich
        you think are so safe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYet even in those days I will not blot you out completely,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd when your people ask, \u2018Why did the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God do all this to us?\u2019 you must reply, \u2018You rejected him and
        gave yourselves to foreign gods in your own land. Now you will serve foreigners
        in a land that is not your own.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: "A Warning for God\u2019s People"
      content: "\u201CMake this announcement to Israel,[COMMENT[0]]and say this to
        Judah:  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'to the house of Jacob. '
        - ft: "The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged
            throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes to the individual patriarch
            and sometimes to the nation."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Listen, you foolish and senseless people,\n\twith eyes that do not
        see\n\tand ears that do not hear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have you no respect for me?\n\tWhy don\u2019t you tremble in my presence?\n\tI,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, define the ocean\u2019s sandy shoreline\n\tas
        an everlasting boundary that the waters cannot cross.\n\tThe waves may toss
        and roar,\n\tbut they can never pass the boundaries I set.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But my people have stubborn and rebellious hearts.\n\tThey have turned
        away and abandoned me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They do not say from the heart,\n\t\u2018Let us live in awe of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God,\n\tfor he gives us rain each spring
        and fall,\n\tassuring us of a harvest when the time is right.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your wickedness has deprived you of these wonderful blessings.\n\tYour
        sin has robbed you of all these good things.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAmong my people are wicked men\n\twho lie in wait for victims
        like a hunter hiding in a blind.\n\tThey continually set traps\n\tto catch
        people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Like a cage filled with birds,\n\ttheir homes are filled with evil
        plots.\n\tAnd now they are great and rich.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are fat and sleek,\n\tand there is no limit to their wicked
        deeds.\n\tThey refuse to provide justice to orphans\n\tand deny the rights
        of the poor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Should I not punish them for this?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CShould
        I not avenge myself against such a nation?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A horrible and shocking thing\n\thas happened in this land\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the prophets give false prophecies,\n\tand the priests rule with
        an iron hand.\n\tWorse yet, my people like it that way!\n\tBut what will
        you do when the end comes?"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Last Warning"
      content: "\u201CRun for your lives, you people of Benjamin!\n\tGet out of Jerusalem!\n\tSound
        the alarm in Tekoa!\n\tSend up a signal at Beth-hakkerem!\n\tA powerful army
        is coming from the north,\n\tcoming with disaster and destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O Jerusalem,[COMMENT[0]] you are my beautiful and delicate daughter\u2014\n\tbut
        I will destroy you!  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Daughter of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "Enemies will surround you, like shepherds camped around the city.\n\tEach
        chooses a place for his troops to devour.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They shout, \u2018Prepare for battle!\n\tAttack at noon!\u2019\n\t\u2018No,
        it\u2019s too late; the day is fading,\n\tand the evening shadows are falling.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Well then, let\u2019s attack at night\n\tand destroy her palaces!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\n\t\u201CCut down the trees for battering rams.\n\tBuild siege ramps
        against the walls of Jerusalem.\n\tThis is the city to be punished,\n\tfor
        she is wicked through and through.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She spouts evil like a fountain.\n\tHer streets echo with the sounds
        of violence and destruction.\n\tI always see her sickness and sores.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to this warning, Jerusalem,\n\tor I will turn from you in
        disgust.\n\tListen, or I will turn you into a heap of ruins,\n\ta land where
        no one lives.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\n\t\u201CEven the few who remain in Israel\n\twill be picked over again,\n\tas
        when a harvester checks each vine a second time\n\tto pick the grapes that
        were missed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Constant Rebellion"
      content: "To whom can I give warning?\n\tWho will listen when I speak?\n\tTheir
        ears are closed,\n\tand they cannot hear.\n\tThey scorn the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tThey
        don\u2019t want to listen at all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now I am filled with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        fury.\n\tYes, I am tired of holding it in!\n\t\u201CI will pour out my fury
        on children playing in the streets\n\tand on gatherings of young men,\n\ton
        husbands and wives\n\tand on those who are old and gray.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their homes will be turned over to their enemies,\n\tas will their
        fields and their wives.\n\tFor I will raise my powerful fist\n\tagainst the
        people of this land,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFrom the least to the greatest,\n\ttheir lives are ruled by
        greed.\n\tFrom prophets to priests,\n\tthey are all frauds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They offer superficial treatments\n\tfor my people\u2019s mortal
        wound.\n\tThey give assurances of peace\n\twhen there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are they ashamed of their disgusting actions?\n\tNot at all\u2014they
        don\u2019t even know how to blush!\n\tTherefore, they will lie among the
        slaughtered.\n\tThey will be brought down when I punish them,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Way"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CStop
        at the crossroads and look around.\n\tAsk for the old, godly way, and walk
        in it.\n\tTravel its path, and you will find rest for your souls.\n\tBut
        you reply, \u2018No, that\u2019s not the road we want!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I posted watchmen over you who said,\n\t\u2018Listen for the sound
        of the alarm.\u2019\n\tBut you replied,\n\t\u2018No! We won\u2019t pay attention!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, listen to this, all you nations.\n\tTake note of
        my people\u2019s situation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen, all the earth!\n\tI will bring disaster on my people.\n\tIt
        is the fruit of their own schemes,\n\tbecause they refuse to listen to me.\n\tThey
        have rejected my word.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There\u2019s no use offering me sweet frankincense from Sheba.\n\tKeep
        your fragrant calamus imported from distant lands!\n\tI will not accept your
        burnt offerings.\n\tYour sacrifices have no pleasing aroma for me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CI
        will put obstacles in my people\u2019s path.\n\tFathers and sons will both
        fall over them.\n\tNeighbors and friends will die together.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: An Invasion from the North
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CLook!
        A great army coming from the north!\n\tA great nation is rising against you
        from far-off lands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are armed with bows and spears.\n\tThey are cruel and show no
        mercy.\n\tThey sound like a roaring sea\n\tas they ride forward on horses.\n\tThey
        are coming in battle formation,\n\tplanning to destroy you, beautiful Jerusalem.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:23 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: daughter of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "We have heard reports about the enemy,\n\tand we wring our hands
        in fright.\n\tPangs of anguish have gripped us,\n\tlike those of a woman
        in labor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t go out to the fields!\n\tDon\u2019t travel on the roads!\n\tThe
        enemy\u2019s sword is everywhere\n\tand terrorizes us at every turn!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, my people, dress yourselves in burlap\n\tand sit among the ashes.\n\tMourn
        and weep bitterly, as for the loss of an only son.\n\tFor suddenly the destroying
        armies will be upon you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CJeremiah, I have made you a tester of metals,[COMMENT[0]]that
        you may determine the quality of my people.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:27 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: a tester of my people a fortress.
    - title: 
      content: "They are the worst kind of rebel,\n\tfull of slander.\n\tThey are
        as hard as bronze and iron,\n\tand they lead others into corruption.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The bellows fiercely fan the flames\n\tto burn out the corruption.\n\tBut
        it does not purify them,\n\tfor the wickedness remains.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will label them \u2018Rejected Silver,\u2019\n\tfor I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        am discarding them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jeremiah Speaks at the Temple
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo to the entrance of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Temple, and give this message to the people: \u2018O Judah, listen to this
        message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t! Listen to it, all of you
        who worship here! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says:\n\t\u201C\u2018Even now, if you quit your evil ways,
        I will let you stay in your own land. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But don\u2019t be fooled by those who promise you safety simply because
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Temple is here. They chant, \u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Temple is here! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Temple is here!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I will be merciful only if you stop your evil thoughts and deeds
        and start treating each other with justice; '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'only if you stop exploiting foreigners, orphans, and widows; only
        if you stop your murdering; and only if you stop harming yourselves by worshiping
        idols. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I will let you stay in this land that I gave to your ancestors
        to keep forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Don\u2019t be fooled into thinking that you will never
        suffer because the Temple is here. It\u2019s a lie! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you really think you can steal, murder, commit adultery, lie,
        and burn incense to Baal and all those other new gods of yours, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and then come here and stand before me in my Temple and chant, \u201CWe
        are safe!\u201D\u2014only to go right back to all those evils again? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t you yourselves admit that this Temple, which bears my
        name, has become a den of thieves? Surely I see all the evil going on there.
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Go now to the place at Shiloh where I once put the Tabernacle
        that bore my name. See what I did there because of all the wickedness of
        my people, the Israelites. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While you were doing these wicked things, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        I spoke to you about it repeatedly, but you would not listen. I called out
        to you, but you refused to answer. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So just as I destroyed Shiloh, I will now destroy this Temple that
        bears my name, this Temple that you trust in for help, this place that I
        gave to you and your ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will send you out of my sight into exile, just as I did your
        relatives, the people of Israel.[COMMENT[0]]\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'of Ephraim, '
        - ft: referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
          body: 
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Persistent Idolatry"
      content: "\u201CPray no more for these people, Jeremiah. Do not weep or pray
        for them, and don\u2019t beg me to help them, for I will not listen to you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t you see what they are doing throughout the towns of Judah
        and in the streets of Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No wonder I am so angry! Watch how the children gather wood and the
        fathers build sacrificial fires. See how the women knead dough and make cakes
        to offer to the Queen of Heaven. And they pour out liquid offerings to their
        other idol gods! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Am I the one they are hurting?\u201D asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        \u201CMost of all, they hurt themselves, to their own shame.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CI
        will pour out my terrible fury on this place. Its people, animals, trees,
        and crops will be consumed by the unquenchable fire of my anger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u201CTake your burnt offerings and your other sacrifices
        and eat them yourselves! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I led your ancestors out of Egypt, it was not burnt offerings
        and sacrifices I wanted from them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what I told them: \u2018Obey me, and I will be your God,
        and you will be my people. Do everything as I say, and all will be well!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut my people would not listen to me. They kept doing whatever
        they wanted, following the stubborn desires of their evil hearts. They went
        backward instead of forward. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From the day your ancestors left Egypt until now, I have continued
        to send my servants, the prophets\u2014day in and day out. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But my people have not listened to me or even tried to hear. They
        have been stubborn and sinful\u2014even worse than their ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTell them all this, but do not expect them to listen. Shout
        out your warnings, but do not expect them to respond. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say to them, \u2018This is the nation whose people will not obey
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God and who refuse to be taught. Truth
        has vanished from among them; it is no longer heard on their lips. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Shave your head in mourning, and weep alone on the mountains. For
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected and forsaken this generation
        that has provoked his fury.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Valley of Slaughter
      content: "\u201CThe people of Judah have sinned before my very eyes,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u201CThey have set up their abominable
        idols right in the Temple that bears my name, defiling it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have built pagan shrines at Topheth, the garbage dump in the
        valley of Ben-Hinnom, and there they burn their sons and daughters in the
        fire. I have never commanded such a horrible deed; it never even crossed
        my mind to command such a thing! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So beware, for the time is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cwhen that garbage dump will no longer be called Topheth or the valley
        of Ben-Hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter. They will bury the bodies in
        Topheth until there is no more room for them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The bodies of my people will be food for the vultures and wild animals,
        and no one will be left to scare them away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: I will put an end to the happy singing and laughter in the streets
        of Jerusalem. The joyful voices of bridegrooms and brides will no longer
        be heard in the towns of Judah. The land will lie in complete desolation.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cthe enemy will break open the graves of the kings and officials of
        Judah, and the graves of the priests, prophets, and common people of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will spread out their bones on the ground before the sun, moon,
        and stars\u2014the gods my people have loved, served, and worshiped. Their
        bones will not be gathered up again or buried but will be scattered on the
        ground like manure. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the people of this evil nation who survive will wish to die rather
        than live where I will send them. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: Deception by False Prophets
      content: "\u201CJeremiah, say to the people, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\n\t\u201C\u2018When people fall down, don\u2019t they get up again?\n\tWhen
        they discover they\u2019re on the wrong road, don\u2019t they turn back?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then why do these people stay on their self-destructive path?\n\tWhy
        do the people of Jerusalem refuse to turn back?\n\tThey cling tightly to
        their lies\n\tand will not turn around.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I listen to their conversations\n\tand don\u2019t hear a word of
        truth.\n\tIs anyone sorry for doing wrong?\n\tDoes anyone say, \u201CWhat
        a terrible thing I have done\u201D?\n\tNo! All are running down the path
        of sin\n\tas swiftly as a horse galloping into battle!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the stork that flies across the sky\n\tknows the time of her
        migration,\n\tas do the turtledove, the swallow, and the crane.[COMMENT[0]]They
        all return at the proper time each year.\n\tBut not my people!\n\tThey do
        not know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s laws.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: The identification of some of these birds is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018How can you say, \u201CWe are wise because we have the
        word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\u201D\n\twhen your teachers
        have twisted it by writing lies?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These wise teachers will fall\n\tinto the trap of their own foolishness,\n\tfor
        they have rejected the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tAre
        they so wise after all?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give their wives to others\n\tand their farms to strangers.\n\tFrom
        the least to the greatest,\n\ttheir lives are ruled by greed.\n\tYes, even
        my prophets and priests are like that.\n\tThey are all frauds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They offer superficial treatments\n\tfor my people\u2019s mortal
        wound.\n\tThey give assurances of peace\n\twhen there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are they ashamed of these disgusting actions?\n\tNot at all\u2014they
        don\u2019t even know how to blush!\n\tTherefore, they will lie among the
        slaughtered.\n\tThey will be brought down when I punish them,\n\tsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will surely consume them.\n\tThere will be no more harvests of
        figs and grapes.\n\tTheir fruit trees will all die.\n\tWhatever I gave them
        will soon be gone.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the people will say,\n\t\u2018Why should we wait here
        to die?\n\tCome, let\u2019s go to the fortified towns and die there.\n\tFor
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God has decreed our destruction\n\tand
        has given us a cup of poison to drink\n\tbecause we sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We hoped for peace, but no peace came.\n\tWe hoped for a time of
        healing, but found only terror.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe snorting of the enemies\u2019 warhorses can be heard\n\tall
        the way from the land of Dan in the north!\n\tThe neighing of their stallions
        makes the whole land tremble.\n\tThey are coming to devour the land and everything
        in it\u2014\n\tcities and people alike.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will send these enemy troops among you\n\tlike poisonous snakes
        you cannot charm.\n\tThey will bite you, and you will die.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jeremiah Weeps for Sinful Judah
      content: "My grief is beyond healing;\n\tmy heart is broken.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to the weeping of my people;\n\tit can be heard all across
        the land.\n\t\u201CHas the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> abandoned Jerusalem?[COMMENT[0]]\u201D
        the people ask.\n\t\u201CIs her King no longer there?\u201D\n\t\u201COh,
        why have they provoked my anger with their carved idols\n\tand their worthless
        foreign gods?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Zion?
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe harvest is finished,\n\tand the summer is gone,\u201D the
        people cry,\n\t\u201Cyet we are not saved!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I hurt with the hurt of my people.\n\tI mourn and am overcome with
        grief.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is there no medicine in Gilead?\n\tIs there no physician there?\n\tWhy
        is there no healing\n\tfor the wounds of my people?"
      comments: []
  - verses:
