    - title: Judgment for Disobedience
      content: "\u201CMy people bend their tongues like bows\n\tto shoot out lies.\n\tThey
        refuse to stand up for the truth.\n\tThey only go from bad to worse.\n\tThey
        do not know me,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBeware of your neighbor!\n\tDon\u2019t even trust your brother!\n\tFor
        brother takes advantage of brother,\n\tand friend slanders friend.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They all fool and defraud each other;\n\tno one tells the truth.\n\tWith
        practiced tongues they tell lies;\n\tthey wear themselves out with all their
        sinning.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They pile lie upon lie\n\tand utterly refuse to acknowledge me,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says:\n\t\u201CSee, I will melt them down in a crucible\n\tand test
        them like metal.\n\tWhat else can I do with my people?[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'with the daughter of my people? '
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: with the evil daughter of my people?
    - title: 
      content: "For their tongues shoot lies like poisoned arrows.\n\tThey speak
        friendly words to their neighbors\n\twhile scheming in their heart to kill
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Should I not punish them for this?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CShould
        I not avenge myself against such a nation?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will weep for the mountains\n\tand wail for the wilderness pastures.\n\tFor
        they are desolate and empty of life;\n\tthe lowing of cattle is heard no
        more;\n\tthe birds and wild animals have all fled.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will make Jerusalem into a heap of ruins,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CIt will be a place haunted by jackals.\n\tThe
        towns of Judah will be ghost towns,\n\twith no one living in them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is wise enough to understand all this? Who has been instructed
        by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and can explain it to others? Why has
        the land been so ruined that no one dares to travel through it?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replies, \u201CThis has happened
        because my people have abandoned my instructions; they have refused to obey
        what I said. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, they have stubbornly followed their own desires and worshiped
        the images of Baal, as their ancestors taught them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: Look! I will feed them with bitterness and
        give them poison to drink. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will scatter them around the world, in places they and their ancestors
        never heard of, and even there I will chase them with the sword until I have
        destroyed them completely.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Weeping in Jerusalem
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\n\t\u201CConsider all this, and call for the mourners.\n\tSend for
        the women who mourn at funerals.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Quick! Begin your weeping!\n\tLet the tears flow from your eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hear the people of Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]] crying in despair,\n\t\u2018We
        are ruined! We are completely humiliated!\n\tWe must leave our land,\n\tbecause
        our homes have been torn down.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "Listen, you women, to the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t;\n\topen
        your ears to what he has to say.\n\tTeach your daughters to wail;\n\tteach
        one another how to lament.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For death has crept in through our windows\n\tand has entered our
        mansions.\n\tIt has killed off the flower of our youth:\n\tChildren no longer
        play in the streets,\n\tand young men no longer gather in the squares.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CBodies
        will be scattered across the fields like clumps of manure,\n\tlike bundles
        of grain after the harvest.\n\tNo one will be left to bury them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CDon\u2019t
        let the wise boast in their wisdom,\n\tor the powerful boast in their power,\n\tor
        the rich boast in their riches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But those who wish to boast\n\tshould boast in this alone:\n\tthat
        they truly know me and understand that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\twho
        demonstrates unfailing love\n\tand who brings justice and righteousness to
        the earth,\n\tand that I delight in these things.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CA time is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cwhen I will punish all those who are circumcised in body but not in
        spirit\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the Egyptians, Edomites, Ammonites, Moabites, the people who live
        in the desert in remote places,[COMMENT[0]] and yes, even the people of Judah.
        And like all these pagan nations, the people of Israel also have uncircumcised
        hearts.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '9:26 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: in the desert and clip the corners of their hair.
  - verses:
    - title: Idolatry Brings Destruction
      content: 'Hear the word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> speaks to you,
        O Israel! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CDo not
        act like the other nations,\n\twho try to read their future in the stars.\n\tDo
        not be afraid of their predictions,\n\teven though other nations are terrified
        by them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their ways are futile and foolish.\n\tThey cut down a tree, and a
        craftsman carves an idol.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They decorate it with gold and silver\n\tand then fasten it securely
        with hammer and nails\n\tso it won\u2019t fall over.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their gods are like\n\thelpless scarecrows in a cucumber field!\n\tThey
        cannot speak,\n\tand they need to be carried because they cannot walk.\n\tDo
        not be afraid of such gods,\n\tfor they can neither harm you nor do you any
        good.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, there is no one like you!\n\tFor
        you are great, and your name is full of power.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who would not fear you, O King of nations?\n\tThat title belongs
        to you alone!\n\tAmong all the wise people of the earth\n\tand in all the
        kingdoms of the world,\n\tthere is no one like you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People who worship idols are stupid and foolish.\n\tThe things they
        worship are made of wood!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They bring beaten sheets of silver from Tarshish\n\tand gold from
        Uphaz,\n\tand they give these materials to skillful craftsmen\n\twho make
        their idols.\n\tThen they dress these gods in royal blue and purple robes\n\tmade
        by expert tailors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the only true God.\n\tHe is
        the living God and the everlasting King!\n\tThe whole earth trembles at his
        anger.\n\tThe nations cannot stand up to his wrath.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say this to those who worship other gods: \u201CYour so-called gods,
        who did not make the heavens and earth, will vanish from the earth and from
        under the heavens.\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: The original text of this verse is in Aramaic.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made the earth by his power,\n\tand
        he preserves it by his wisdom.\n\tWith his own understanding\n\the stretched
        out the heavens.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When he speaks in the thunder,\n\tthe heavens roar with rain.\n\tHe
        causes the clouds to rise over the earth.\n\tHe sends the lightning with
        the rain\n\tand releases the wind from his storehouses.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The whole human race is foolish and has no knowledge!\n\tThe craftsmen
        are disgraced by the idols they make,\n\tfor their carefully shaped works
        are a fraud.\n\tThese idols have no breath or power.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Idols are worthless; they are ridiculous lies!\n\tOn the day of reckoning
        they will all be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the God of Israel[COMMENT[0]] is no idol!\n\tHe is the Creator
        of everything that exists,\n\tincluding Israel, his own special possession.\n\tThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies is his name!  "
      comments:
