  - verses:
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Broken Covenant"
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRemind the people of Judah and Jerusalem about the terms of
        my covenant with them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of Israel, says: Cursed is anyone who does not obey the terms of
        my covenant! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I said to your ancestors when I brought them out of the iron-smelting
        furnace of Egypt, \u201CIf you obey me and do whatever I command you, then
        you will be my people, and I will be your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I said this so I could keep my promise to your ancestors to give
        you a land flowing with milk and honey\u2014the land you live in today.\u2019\u201D\n\tThen
        I replied, \u201CAmen, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t! May it be so.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CBroadcast this message
        in the streets of Jerusalem. Go from town to town throughout the land and
        say, \u2018Remember the ancient covenant, and do everything it requires. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I solemnly warned your ancestors when I brought them out of Egypt,
        \u201CObey me!\u201D I have repeated this warning over and over to this day, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but your ancestors did not listen or even pay attention. Instead,
        they stubbornly followed their own evil desires. And because they refused
        to obey, I brought upon them all the curses described in this covenant.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Again the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to me and said, \u201CI
        have discovered a conspiracy against me among the people of Judah and Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have returned to the sins of their ancestors. They have refused
        to listen to me and are worshiping other gods. Israel and Judah have both
        broken the covenant I made with their ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I am
        going to bring calamity upon them, and they will not escape. Though they
        beg for mercy, I will not listen to their cries. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the people of Judah and Jerusalem will pray to their idols and
        burn incense before them. But the idols will not save them when disaster
        strikes! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look now, people of Judah; you have as many gods as you have towns.
        You have as many altars of shame\u2014altars for burning incense to your
        god Baal\u2014as there are streets in Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPray no more for these people, Jeremiah. Do not weep or pray
        for them, for I will not listen to them when they cry out to me in distress.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat right do my beloved people have to come to my Temple,\n\twhen
        they have done so many immoral things?\n\tCan their vows and sacrifices prevent
        their destruction?\n\tThey actually rejoice in doing evil!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, once called them a thriving
        olive tree,\n\tbeautiful to see and full of good fruit.\n\tBut now I have
        sent the fury of their enemies\n\tto burn them with fire,\n\tleaving them
        charred and broken.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        who planted this olive tree, have ordered it destroyed. For the people of
        Israel and Judah have done evil, arousing my anger by burning incense to
        Baal.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Plot against Jeremiah
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told me about the plots my enemies
        were making against me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was like a lamb being led to the slaughter. I had no idea that
        they were planning to kill me! \u201CLet\u2019s destroy this man and all
        his words,\u201D they said. \u201CLet\u2019s cut him down, so his name will
        be forgotten forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,\n\tyou make
        righteous judgments,\n\tand you examine the deepest thoughts and secrets.\n\tLet
        me see your vengeance against them,\n\tfor I have committed my cause to you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about the men of
        Anathoth who wanted me dead. They had said, \u201CWe will kill you if you
        do not stop prophesying in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says about them: \u201CI will punish them! Their young men will die
        in battle, and their boys and girls will starve to death. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Not one of these plotters from Anathoth will survive, for I will
        bring disaster upon them when their time of punishment comes.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Justice"
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you always give me justice\n\twhen
        I bring a case before you.\n\tSo let me bring you this complaint:\n\tWhy
        are the wicked so prosperous?\n\tWhy are evil people so happy?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have planted them,\n\tand they have taken root and prospered.\n\tYour
        name is on their lips,\n\tbut you are far from their hearts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But as for me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you know my heart.\n\tYou
        see me and test my thoughts.\n\tDrag these people away like sheep to be butchered!\n\tSet
        them aside to be slaughtered!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How long must this land mourn?\n\tEven the grass in the fields has
        withered.\n\tThe wild animals and birds have disappeared\n\tbecause of the
        evil in the land.\n\tFor the people have said,\n\t\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord
        </smallcaps>\n\tdoesn\u2019t see what\u2019s ahead for us!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Reply to Jeremiah"
      content: "\u201CIf racing against mere men makes you tired,\n\thow will you
        race against horses?\n\tIf you stumble and fall on open ground,\n\twhat will
        you do in the thickets near the Jordan?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even your brothers, members of your own family,\n\thave turned against
        you.\n\tThey plot and raise complaints against you.\n\tDo not trust them,\n\tno
        matter how pleasantly they speak.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have abandoned my people, my special possession.\n\tI have
        surrendered my dearest ones to their enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My chosen people have roared at me like a lion of the forest,\n\tso
        I have treated them with contempt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My chosen people act like speckled vultures,[COMMENT[0]]but they
        themselves are surrounded by vultures.\n\tBring on the wild animals to pick
        their corpses clean!  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: speckled hyenas.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMany rulers have ravaged my vineyard,\n\ttrampling down the
        vines\n\tand turning all its beauty into a barren wilderness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They have made it an empty wasteland;\n\tI hear its mournful cry.\n\tThe
        whole land is desolate,\n\tand no one even cares.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On all the bare hilltops,\n\tdestroying armies can be seen.\n\tThe
        sword of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> devours people\n\tfrom one end of
        the nation to the other.\n\tNo one will escape!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My people have planted wheat\n\tbut are harvesting thorns.\n\tThey
        have worn themselves out,\n\tbut it has done them no good.\n\tThey will harvest
        a crop of shame\n\tbecause of the fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "A Message for Israel\u2019s Neighbors"
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CI will
        uproot from their land all the evil nations reaching out for the possession
        I gave my people Israel. And I will uproot Judah from among them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But afterward I will return and have compassion on all of them. I
        will bring them home to their own lands again, each nation to its own possession. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if these nations truly learn the ways of my people, and if they
        learn to swear by my name, saying, \u2018As surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives\u2019 (just as they taught my people to swear by the name of Baal),
        then they will be given a place among my people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But any nation who refuses to obey me will be uprooted and destroyed.
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Linen Loincloth"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CGo
        and buy a linen loincloth and put it on, but do not wash it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I bought the loincloth as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> directed
        me, and I put it on.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me another message: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTake the linen loincloth you are wearing, and go to the Euphrates
        River.[COMMENT[0]] Hide it there in a hole in the rocks.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '13:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Perath; '
        - ft: also in 13:5, 6, 7.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'So I went and hid it by the Euphrates as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had instructed me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A long time afterward the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,
        \u201CGo back to the Euphrates and get the loincloth I told you to hide there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I went to the Euphrates and dug it out of the hole where I had
        hidden it. But now it was rotting and falling apart. The loincloth was good
        for nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I received this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: This shows
        how I will rot away the pride of Judah and Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These wicked people refuse to listen to me. They stubbornly follow
        their own desires and worship other gods. Therefore, they will become like
        this loincloth\u2014good for nothing! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As a loincloth clings to a man\u2019s waist, so I created Judah and
        Israel to cling to me, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. They were
        to be my people, my pride, my glory\u2014an honor to my name. But they would
        not listen to me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo tell them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of Israel, says: May all your jars be filled with wine.\u2019 And
        they will reply, \u2018Of course! Jars are made to be filled with wine!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen tell them, \u2018No, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        means: I will fill everyone in this land with drunkenness\u2014from the king
        sitting on David\u2019s throne to the priests and the prophets, right down
        to the common people of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will smash them against each other, even parents against children,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. I will not let my pity or mercy
        or compassion keep me from destroying them.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Warning against Pride
      content: "Listen and pay attention!\n\tDo not be arrogant, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Give glory to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God\n\tbefore
        it is too late.\n\tAcknowledge him before he brings darkness upon you,\n\tcausing
        you to stumble and fall on the darkening mountains.\n\tFor then, when you
        look for light,\n\tyou will find only terrible darkness and gloom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if you still refuse to listen,\n\tI will weep alone because of
        your pride.\n\tMy eyes will overflow with tears,\n\tbecause the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        flock will be led away into exile.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say to the king and his mother,\n\t\u201CCome down from your thrones\n\tand
        sit in the dust,\n\tfor your glorious crowns\n\twill soon be snatched from
        your heads.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The towns of the Negev will close their gates,\n\tand no one will
        be able to open them.\n\tThe people of Judah will be taken away as captives.\n\tAll
        will be carried into exile.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Open up your eyes and see\n\tthe armies marching down from the north!\n\tWhere
        is your flock\u2014\n\tyour beautiful flock\u2014\n\tthat he gave you to
        care for?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What will you say when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> takes the
        allies you have cultivated\n\tand appoints them as your rulers?\n\tPangs
        of anguish will grip you,\n\tlike those of a woman in labor!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You may ask yourself,\n\t\u201CWhy is all this happening to me?\u201D\n\tIt
        is because of your many sins!\n\tThat is why you have been stripped\n\tand
        raped by invading armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can an Ethiopian[COMMENT[0]] change the color of his skin?\n\tCan
        a leopard take away its spots?\n\tNeither can you start doing good,\n\tfor
        you have always done evil.  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:23 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: a Cushite.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will scatter you like chaff\n\tthat is blown away by the
        desert winds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is your allotment,\n\tthe portion I have assigned to you,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cfor you have forgotten me,\n\tputting
        your trust in false gods.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I myself will strip you\n\tand expose you to shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have seen your adultery and lust,\n\tand your disgusting idol worship
        out in the fields and on the hills.\n\tWhat sorrow awaits you, Jerusalem!\n\tHow
        long before you are pure?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Terrible Drought"
      content: "This message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        explaining why he was holding back the rain:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CJudah wilts;\n\tcommerce at the city gates grinds to a halt.\n\tAll
        the people sit on the ground in mourning,\n\tand a great cry rises from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The nobles send servants to get water,\n\tbut all the wells are dry.\n\tThe
        servants return with empty pitchers,\n\tconfused and desperate,\n\tcovering
        their heads in grief.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The ground is parched\n\tand cracked for lack of rain.\n\tThe farmers
        are deeply troubled;\n\tthey, too, cover their heads.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the doe abandons her newborn fawn\n\tbecause there is no grass
        in the field.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wild donkeys stand on the bare hills\n\tpanting like thirsty
        jackals.\n\tThey strain their eyes looking for grass,\n\tbut there is none
        to be found.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people say, \u201COur wickedness has caught up with us, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tbut
        help us for the sake of your own reputation.\n\tWe have turned away from
        you\n\tand sinned against you again and again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O Hope of Israel, our Savior in times of trouble,\n\twhy are you
        like a stranger to us?\n\tWhy are you like a traveler passing through the
        land,\n\tstopping only for the night?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are you also confused?\n\tIs our champion helpless to save us?\n\tYou
        are right here among us, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tWe are known
        as your people.\n\tPlease don\u2019t abandon us now!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to his people:\n\t\u201CYou
        love to wander far from me\n\tand do not restrain yourselves.\n\tTherefore,
        I will no longer accept you as my people.\n\tNow I will remember all your
        wickedness\n\tand will punish you for your sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: ' Forbids Jeremiah to Intercede'
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CDo not pray
        for these people anymore. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they fast, I will pay no attention. When they present their
        burnt offerings and grain offerings to me, I will not accept them. Instead,
        I will devour them with war, famine, and disease.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, their
        prophets are telling them, \u2018All is well\u2014no war or famine will come.
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will surely send you peace.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CThese prophets are
        telling lies in my name. I did not send them or tell them to speak. I did
        not give them any messages. They prophesy of visions and revelations they
        have never seen or heard. They speak foolishness made up in their own lying
        hearts. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I will
        punish these lying prophets, for they have spoken in my name even though
        I never sent them. They say that no war or famine will come, but they themselves
        will die by war and famine! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As for the people to whom they prophesy\u2014their bodies will be
        thrown out into the streets of Jerusalem, victims of famine and war. There
        will be no one left to bury them. Husbands, wives, sons, and daughters\u2014all
        will be gone. For I will pour out their own wickedness on them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now, Jeremiah, say this to them:\n\t\u201CNight and day my eyes overflow
        with tears.\n\tI cannot stop weeping,\n\tfor my virgin daughter\u2014my precious
        people\u2014\n\thas been struck down\n\tand lies mortally wounded.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If I go out into the fields,\n\tI see the bodies of people slaughtered
        by the enemy.\n\tIf I walk the city streets,\n\tI see people who have died
        of starvation.\n\tThe prophets and priests continue with their work,\n\tbut
        they don\u2019t know what they\u2019re doing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Prayer for Healing
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have you completely rejected Judah?\n\tDo
        you really hate Jerusalem?[COMMENT[0]]Why have you wounded us past all hope
        of healing?\n\tWe hoped for peace, but no peace came.\n\tWe hoped for a time
        of healing, but found only terror.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Zion?
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, we confess our wickedness\n\tand
        that of our ancestors, too.\n\tWe all have sinned against you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the sake of your reputation, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        do not abandon us.\n\tDo not disgrace your own glorious throne.\n\tPlease
        remember us,\n\tand do not break your covenant with us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can any of the worthless foreign gods send us rain?\n\tDoes it fall
        from the sky by itself?\n\tNo, you are the one, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God!\n\tOnly you can do such things.\n\tSo we will wait for you to help
        us."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Inevitable Doom"
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CEven if Moses
        and Samuel stood before me pleading for these people, I wouldn\u2019t help
        them. Away with them! Get them out of my sight! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if they say to you, \u2018But where can we go?\u2019 tell them,
        \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201C\u2018Those
        who are destined for death, to death;\n\tthose who are destined for war,
        to war;\n\tthose who are destined for famine, to famine;\n\tthose who are
        destined for captivity, to captivity.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will send four kinds of destroyers against them,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u201CI will send the sword to kill,
        the dogs to drag away, the vultures to devour, and the wild animals to finish
        up what is left. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of the wicked things Manasseh son of Hezekiah, king of Judah,
        did in Jerusalem, I will make my people an object of horror to all the kingdoms
        of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho will feel sorry for you, Jerusalem?\n\tWho will weep for
        you?\n\tWho will even bother to ask how you are?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have abandoned me\n\tand turned your back on me,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CTherefore, I will raise my
        fist to destroy you.\n\tI am tired of always giving you another chance.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will winnow you like grain at the gates of your cities\n\tand take
        away the children you hold dear.\n\tI will destroy my own people,\n\tbecause
        they refuse to change their evil ways.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There will be more widows\n\tthan the grains of sand on the seashore.\n\tAt
        noontime I will bring a destroyer\n\tagainst the mothers of young men.\n\tI
        will cause anguish and terror\n\tto come upon them suddenly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The mother of seven grows faint and gasps for breath;\n\ther sun
        has gone down while it is still day.\n\tShe sits childless now,\n\tdisgraced
        and humiliated.\n\tAnd I will hand over those who are left\n\tto be killed
        by the enemy.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      content: "Then I said,\n\t\u201CWhat sorrow is mine, my mother.\n\tOh, that
        I had died at birth!\n\tI am hated everywhere I go.\n\tI am neither a lender
        who threatens to foreclose\n\tnor a borrower who refuses to pay\u2014\n\tyet
        they all curse me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replied,\n\t\u201CI will take care
        of you, Jeremiah.\n\tYour enemies will ask you to plead on their behalf\n\tin
        times of trouble and distress.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can a man break a bar of iron from the north,\n\tor a bar of bronze?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At no cost to them,\n\tI will hand over your wealth and treasures\n\tas
        plunder to your enemies,\n\tfor sin runs rampant in your land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will tell your enemies to take you\n\tas captives to a foreign
        land.\n\tFor my anger blazes like a fire\n\tthat will burn forever.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in some Hebrew manuscripts (see also 17:4); most Hebrew manuscripts
            read '
          body: will burn against you.
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said,\n\t\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you know what\u2019s
        happening to me.\n\tPlease step in and help me. Punish my persecutors!\n\tPlease
        give me time; don\u2019t let me die young.\n\tIt\u2019s for your sake that
        I am suffering.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I discovered your words, I devoured them.\n\tThey are my joy
        and my heart\u2019s delight,\n\tfor I bear your name,\n\tO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I never joined the people in their merry feasts.\n\tI sat alone because
        your hand was on me.\n\tI was filled with indignation at their sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why then does my suffering continue?\n\tWhy is my wound so incurable?\n\tYour
        help seems as uncertain as a seasonal brook,\n\tlike a spring that has gone
        dry.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> responds:\n\t\u201CIf
        you return to me, I will restore you\n\tso you can continue to serve me.\n\tIf
        you speak good words rather than worthless ones,\n\tyou will be my spokesman.\n\tYou
        must influence them;\n\tdo not let them influence you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will fight against you like an attacking army,\n\tbut I will
        make you as secure as a fortified wall of bronze.\n\tThey will not conquer
        you,\n\tfor I am with you to protect and rescue you.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, I will certainly keep you safe from these wicked men.\n\tI will
        rescue you from their cruel hands.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jeremiah Forbidden to Marry
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me another message. He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not get married or have children in this place. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about the children
        born here in this city and about their mothers and fathers: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will die from terrible diseases. No one will mourn for them
        or bury them, and they will lie scattered on the ground like manure. They
        will die from war and famine, and their bodies will be food for the vultures
        and wild animals.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Coming Punishment"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CDo not go
        to funerals to mourn and show sympathy for these people, for I have removed
        my protection and peace from them. I have taken away my unfailing love and
        my mercy. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Both the great and the lowly will die in this land. No one will bury
        them or mourn for them. Their friends will not cut themselves in sorrow or
        shave their heads in sadness. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one will offer a meal to comfort those who mourn for the dead\u2014not
        even at the death of a mother or father. No one will send a cup of wine to
        console them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd do not go to their feasts and parties. Do not eat and drink
        with them at all. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: In your own lifetime, before your very eyes,
        I will put an end to the happy singing and laughter in this land. The joyful
        voices of bridegrooms and brides will no longer be heard.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you tell the people all these things, they will ask, \u2018Why
        has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> decreed such terrible things against
        us? What have we done to deserve such treatment? What is our sin against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen you will give them the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        reply: \u2018It is because your ancestors were unfaithful to me. They worshiped
        other gods and served them. They abandoned me and did not obey my word. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And you are even worse than your ancestors! You stubbornly follow
        your own evil desires and refuse to listen to me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will throw you out of this land and send you into a foreign
        land where you and your ancestors have never been. There you can worship
        idols day and night\u2014and I will grant you no favors!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: Hope despite the Disaster
      content: "\u201CBut the time is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cwhen people who are taking an oath will no longer say, \u2018As surely
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, who rescued the people of Israel
        from the land of Egypt.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, they will say, \u2018As surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, who brought the people of Israel back to their own land from the land
        of the north and from all the countries to which he had exiled them.\u2019
        For I will bring them back to this land that I gave their ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut now I am sending for many fishermen who will catch them,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u201CI am sending for hunters
        who will hunt them down in the mountains, hills, and caves. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am watching them closely, and I see every sin. They cannot hope
        to hide from me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will double their punishment for all their sins, because they have
        defiled my land with lifeless images of their detestable gods and have filled
        my territory with their evil deeds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer of Confidence"
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you are my strength and fortress,\n\tmy
        refuge in the day of trouble!\n\tNations from around the world\n\twill come
        to you and say,\n\t\u201COur ancestors left us a foolish heritage,\n\tfor
        they worshiped worthless idols.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can people make their own gods?\n\tThese are not real gods at all!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\n\t\u201CNow I will show them
        my power;\n\tnow I will show them my might.\n\tAt last they will know and
        understand\n\tthat I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Sin and Punishment"
      content: "\u201CThe sin of Judah\n\tis inscribed with an iron chisel\u2014\n\tengraved
        with a diamond point on their stony hearts\n\tand on the corners of their
        altars.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even their children go to worship\n\tat their pagan altars and Asherah
        poles,\n\tbeneath every green tree\n\tand on every high hill.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will hand over my holy mountain\u2014\n\talong with all your
        wealth and treasures\n\tand your pagan shrines\u2014\n\tas plunder to your
        enemies,\n\tfor sin runs rampant in your land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wonderful possession I have reserved for you\n\twill slip from
        your hands.\n\tI will tell your enemies to take you\n\tas captives to a foreign
        land.\n\tFor my anger blazes like a fire\n\tthat will burn forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Lord
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CCursed
        are those who put their trust in mere humans,\n\twho rely on human strength\n\tand
        turn their hearts away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are like stunted shrubs in the desert,\n\twith no hope for the
        future.\n\tThey will live in the barren wilderness,\n\tin an uninhabited
        salty land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut blessed are those who trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand
        have made the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their hope and confidence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are like trees planted along a riverbank,\n\twith roots that
        reach deep into the water.\n\tSuch trees are not bothered by the heat\n\tor
        worried by long months of drought.\n\tTheir leaves stay green,\n\tand they
        never stop producing fruit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe human heart is the most deceitful of all things,\n\tand
        desperately wicked.\n\tWho really knows how bad it is?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, search all hearts\n\tand
        examine secret motives.\n\tI give all people their due rewards,\n\taccording
        to what their actions deserve.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Lord
      content: "Like a partridge that hatches eggs she has not laid,\n\tso are those
        who get their wealth by unjust means.\n\tAt midlife they will lose their
        riches;\n\tin the end, they will become poor old fools.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But we worship at your throne\u2014\n\teternal, high, and glorious!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the hope of Israel,\n\tall who
        turn away from you will be disgraced.\n\tThey will be buried in the dust
        of the earth,\n\tfor they have abandoned the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the fountain of living water.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, if you heal me, I will be truly
        healed;\n\tif you save me, I will be truly saved.\n\tMy praises are for you
        alone!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People scoff at me and say,\n\t\u201CWhat is this \u2018message from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019 you talk about?\n\tWhy don\u2019t
        your predictions come true?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, I have not abandoned my job\n\tas
        a shepherd for your people.\n\tI have not urged you to send disaster.\n\tYou
        have heard everything I\u2019ve said.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, don\u2019t terrorize me!\n\tYou
        alone are my hope in the day of disaster.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Bring shame and dismay on all who persecute me,\n\tbut don\u2019t
        let me experience shame and dismay.\n\tBring a day of terror on them.\n\tYes,
        bring double destruction upon them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: Observing the Sabbath
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CGo
        and stand in the gates of Jerusalem, first in the gate where the king goes
        in and out, and then in each of the other gates. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say to all the people, \u2018Listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        you kings of Judah and all you people of Judah and everyone living in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Listen to my warning!
        Stop carrying on your trade at Jerusalem\u2019s gates on the Sabbath day. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not do your work on the Sabbath, but make it a holy day. I gave
        this command to your ancestors, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but they did not listen or obey. They stubbornly refused to pay attention
        or accept my discipline.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018But if you obey me, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        and do not carry on your trade at the gates or work on the Sabbath day, and
        if you keep it holy, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then kings and their officials will go in and out of these gates
        forever. There will always be a descendant of David sitting on the throne
        here in Jerusalem. Kings and their officials will always ride in and out
        among the people of Judah in chariots and on horses, and this city will remain
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And from all around Jerusalem, from the towns of Judah and Benjamin,
        from the western foothills[COMMENT[0]] and the hill country and the Negev,
        the people will come with their burnt offerings and sacrifices. They will
        bring their grain offerings, frankincense, and thanksgiving offerings to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Temple.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:26 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Shephelah.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018But if you do not listen to me and refuse to keep the
        Sabbath holy, and if on the Sabbath day you bring loads of merchandise through
        the gates of Jerusalem just as on other days, then I will set fire to these
        gates. The fire will spread to the palaces, and no one will be able to put
        out the roaring flames.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Potter and the Clay
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo down to the potter\u2019s shop, and I will speak to you
        there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I did as he told me and found the potter working at his wheel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the jar he was making did not turn out as he had hoped, so he
        crushed it into a lump of clay again and started over.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me this message: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO Israel, can I not do to you as this potter has done to his
        clay? As the clay is in the potter\u2019s hand, so are you in my hand. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If I announce that a certain nation or kingdom is to be uprooted,
        torn down, and destroyed, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but then that nation renounces its evil ways, I will not destroy
        it as I had planned. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if I announce that I will plant and build up a certain nation
        or kingdom, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but then that nation turns to evil and refuses to obey me, I will
        not bless it as I said I would.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, Jeremiah, go and warn all Judah and Jerusalem. Say
        to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I am planning
        disaster for you instead of good. So turn from your evil ways, each of you,
        and do what is right.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people replied, \u201CDon\u2019t waste your breath. We will
        continue to live as we want to, stubbornly following our own evil desires.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CHas
        anyone ever heard of such a thing,\n\teven among the pagan nations?\n\tMy
        virgin daughter Israel\n\thas done something terrible!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does the snow ever disappear from the mountaintops of Lebanon?\n\tDo
        the cold streams flowing from those distant mountains ever run dry?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But my people are not so reliable, for they have deserted me;\n\tthey
        burn incense to worthless idols.\n\tThey have stumbled off the ancient highways\n\tand
        walk in muddy paths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, their land will become desolate,\n\ta monument to their
        stupidity.\n\tAll who pass by will be astonished\n\tand will shake their
        heads in amazement.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will scatter my people before their enemies\n\tas the east wind
        scatters dust.\n\tAnd in all their trouble I will turn my back on them\n\tand
        refuse to notice their distress.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Plot against Jeremiah
      content: "Then the people said, \u201CCome on, let\u2019s plot a way to stop
        Jeremiah. We have plenty of priests and wise men and prophets. We don\u2019t
        need him to teach the word and give us advice and prophecies. Let\u2019s
        spread rumors about him and ignore what he says.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, hear me and help me!\n\tListen
        to what my enemies are saying.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Should they repay evil for good?\n\tThey have dug a pit to kill me,\n\tthough
        I pleaded for them\n\tand tried to protect them from your anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So let their children starve!\n\tLet them die by the sword!\n\tLet
        their wives become childless widows.\n\tLet their old men die in a plague,\n\tand
        let their young men be killed in battle!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let screaming be heard from their homes\n\tas warriors come suddenly
        upon them.\n\tFor they have dug a pit for me\n\tand have hidden traps along
        my path.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you know all about their murderous
        plots against me.\n\tDon\u2019t forgive their crimes and blot out their sins.\n\tLet
        them die before you.\n\tDeal with them in your anger."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Shattered Jar"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CGo
        and buy a clay jar. Then ask some of the leaders of the people and of the
        priests to follow you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Go out through the Gate of Broken Pots to the garbage dump in the
        valley of Ben-Hinnom, and give them this message. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say to them, \u2018Listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        you kings of Judah and citizens of Jerusalem! This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: I will bring a terrible
        disaster on this place, and the ears of those who hear about it will ring!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018For Israel has forsaken me and turned this valley into
        a place of wickedness. The people burn incense to foreign gods\u2014idols
        never before acknowledged by this generation, by their ancestors, or by the
        kings of Judah. And they have filled this place with the blood of innocent
        children. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have built pagan shrines to Baal, and there they burn their
        sons as sacrifices to Baal. I have never commanded such a horrible deed;
        it never even crossed my mind to command such a thing! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So beware, for the time is coming, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        when this garbage dump will no longer be called Topheth or the valley of
        Ben-Hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018For I will upset the careful plans of Judah and Jerusalem.
        I will allow the people to be slaughtered by invading armies, and I will
        leave their dead bodies as food for the vultures and wild animals. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will reduce Jerusalem to ruins, making it a monument to their stupidity.
        All who pass by will be astonished and will gasp at the destruction they
        see there. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will see to it that your enemies lay siege to the city until all
        the food is gone. Then those trapped inside will eat their own sons and daughters
        and friends. They will be driven to utter despair.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs these men watch you, Jeremiah, smash the jar you brought. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then say to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says: As this jar lies shattered, so I will shatter
        the people of Judah and Jerusalem beyond all hope of repair. They will bury
        the bodies here in Topheth, the garbage dump, until there is no more room
        for them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what I will do to this place and its people, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        I will cause this city to become defiled like Topheth. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, all the houses in Jerusalem, including the palace of Judah\u2019s
        kings, will become like Topheth\u2014all the houses where you burned incense
        on the rooftops to your star gods, and where liquid offerings were poured
        out to your idols.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jeremiah returned from Topheth, the garbage dump where he had
        delivered this message, and he stopped in front of the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        He said to the people there, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018I will bring disaster upon this city
        and its surrounding towns as I promised, because you have stubbornly refused
        to listen to me.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jeremiah and Pashhur
      content: "Now Pashhur son of Immer, the priest in charge of the Temple of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, heard what Jeremiah was prophesying. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So he arrested Jeremiah the prophet and had him whipped and put in
        stocks at the Benjamin Gate of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Temple.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The next day, when Pashhur finally released him, Jeremiah said, \u201CPashhur,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has changed your name. From now on you are
        to be called \u2018The Man Who Lives in Terror.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Magor-missabib, '
        - ft: "which means \u201Csurrounded by terror\u201D; also in 20:10."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018I will
        send terror upon you and all your friends, and you will watch as they are
        slaughtered by the swords of the enemy. I will hand the people of Judah over
        to the king of Babylon. He will take them captive to Babylon or run them
        through with the sword. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will let your enemies plunder Jerusalem. All the famed treasures
        of the city\u2014the precious jewels and gold and silver of your kings\u2014will
        be carried off to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As for you, Pashhur, you and all your household will go as captives
        to Babylon. There you will die and be buried, you and all your friends to
        whom you prophesied that everything would be all right.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you misled me,\n\tand I allowed
        myself to be misled.\n\tYou are stronger than I am,\n\tand you overpowered
        me.\n\tNow I am mocked every day;\n\teveryone laughs at me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I speak, the words burst out.\n\t\u201CViolence and destruction!\u201D
        I shout.\n\tSo these messages from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\thave
        made me a household joke.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if I say I\u2019ll never mention the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tor
        speak in his name,\n\this word burns in my heart like a fire.\n\tIt\u2019s
        like a fire in my bones!\n\tI am worn out trying to hold it in!\n\tI can\u2019t
        do it!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have heard the many rumors about me.\n\tThey call me \u201CThe
        Man Who Lives in Terror.\u201D\n\tThey threaten, \u201CIf you say anything,
        we will report it.\u201D\n\tEven my old friends are watching me,\n\twaiting
        for a fatal slip.\n\t\u201CHe will trap himself,\u201D they say,\n\t\u201Cand
        then we will get our revenge on him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> stands beside me like a great
        warrior.\n\tBefore him my persecutors will stumble.\n\tThey cannot defeat
        me.\n\tThey will fail and be thoroughly humiliated.\n\tTheir dishonor will
        never be forgotten.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,\n\tyou test
        those who are righteous,\n\tand you examine the deepest thoughts and secrets.\n\tLet
        me see your vengeance against them,\n\tfor I have committed my cause to you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\n\tPraise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\n\tFor
        though I was poor and needy,\n\the rescued me from my oppressors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet I curse the day I was born!\n\tMay no one celebrate the day of
        my birth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I curse the messenger who told my father,\n\t\u201CGood news\u2014you
        have a son!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let him be destroyed like the cities of old\n\tthat the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        overthrew without mercy.\n\tTerrify him all day long with battle shouts,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "because he did not kill me at birth.\n\tOh, that I had died in my
        mother\u2019s womb,\n\tthat her body had been my grave!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why was I ever born?\n\tMy entire life has been filled\n\twith trouble,
        sorrow, and shame."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: No Deliverance from Babylon
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke through Jeremiah when King
        Zedekiah sent Pashhur son of Malkijah and Zephaniah son of Maaseiah, the
        priest, to speak with him. They begged Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPlease speak to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for us and
        ask him to help us. King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[0]] of Babylon is attacking
        Judah. Perhaps the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be gracious and do a
        mighty miracle as he has done in the past. Perhaps he will force Nebuchadnezzar
        to withdraw his armies.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar; also in 21:7.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Jeremiah replied, \u201CGo back to King Zedekiah and tell him, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of
        Israel, says: I will make your weapons useless against the king of Babylon
        and the Babylonians[COMMENT[0]] who are outside your walls attacking you.
        In fact, I will bring your enemies right into the heart of this city. "
      comments:
      - number: '21:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Chaldeans; '
        - ft: also in 21:9.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'I myself will fight against you with a strong hand and a powerful
        arm, for I am very angry. You have made me furious! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will send a terrible plague upon this city, and both people and
        animals will die. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And after all that, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, I will
        hand over King Zedekiah, his staff, and everyone else in the city who survives
        the disease, war, and famine. I will hand them over to King Nebuchadnezzar
        of Babylon and to their other enemies. He will slaughter them and show them
        no mercy, pity, or compassion.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTell all the people, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: Take your choice of life or death! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everyone who stays in Jerusalem will die from war, famine, or disease,
        but those who go out and surrender to the Babylonians will live. Their reward
        will be life! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I have decided to bring disaster and not good upon this city,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. It will be handed over to the king
        of Babylon, and he will reduce it to ashes.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Judgment on Judah\u2019s Kings"
      content: "\u201CSay to the royal family of Judah, \u2018Listen to this message
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to the dynasty
        of David:\n\t\u201C\u2018Give justice each morning to the people you judge!\n\tHelp
        those who have been robbed;\n\trescue them from their oppressors.\n\tOtherwise,
        my anger will burn like an unquenchable fire\n\tbecause of all your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will personally fight against the people in Jerusalem,\n\tthat
        mighty fortress\u2014\n\tthe people who boast, \u201CNo one can touch us
        here.\n\tNo one can break in here.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I myself will punish you for your sinfulness,\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tI
        will light a fire in your forests\n\tthat will burn up everything around
        you.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "A Message for Judah\u2019s Kings"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CGo
        over and speak directly to the king of Judah. Say to him, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        you king of Judah, sitting on David\u2019s throne. Let your attendants and
        your people listen, too. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Be fair-minded
        and just. Do what is right! Help those who have been robbed; rescue them
        from their oppressors. Quit your evil deeds! Do not mistreat foreigners,
        orphans, and widows. Stop murdering the innocent! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you obey me, there will always be a descendant of David sitting
        on the throne here in Jerusalem. The king will ride through the palace gates
        in chariots and on horses, with his parade of attendants and subjects. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you refuse to pay attention to this warning, I swear by my
        own name, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, that this palace will
        become a pile of rubble.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about the Palace
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says concerning
        Judah\u2019s royal palace:\n\t\u201CI love you as much as fruitful Gilead\n\tand
        the green forests of Lebanon.\n\tBut I will turn you into a desert,\n\twith
        no one living within your walls.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will call for wreckers,\n\twho will bring out their tools to dismantle
        you.\n\tThey will tear out all your fine cedar beams\n\tand throw them on
        the fire.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPeople from many nations will pass by the ruins of this city
        and say to one another, \u2018Why did the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> destroy
        such a great city?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the answer will be, \u2018Because they violated their covenant
        with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God by worshiping other gods.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Jehoahaz
      content: "Do not weep for the dead king or mourn his loss.\n\tInstead, weep
        for the captive king being led away!\n\tFor he will never return to see his
        native land again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about Jehoahaz,[COMMENT[0]]
        who succeeded his father, King Josiah, and was taken away as a captive: \u201CHe
        will never return. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Shallum, '
        - ft: another name for Jehoahaz.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "He will die in a distant land and will never again see his own country.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Jehoiakim
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CWhat sorrow awaits
        Jehoiakim,[COMMENT[0]]who builds his palace with forced labor.[COMMENT[1]]He
        builds injustice into its walls,\n\tfor he makes his neighbors work for nothing.\n\tHe
        does not pay them for their labor.  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:13a '
        contents:
        - ft: The brother and successor of the exiled Jehoahaz. See 22:18.
          body: 
      - number: '22:13b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: by unrighteousness.
    - title: 
      content: "He says, \u2018I will build a magnificent palace\n\twith huge rooms
        and many windows.\n\tI will panel it throughout with fragrant cedar\n\tand
        paint it a lovely red.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But a beautiful cedar palace does not make a great king!\n\tYour
        father, Josiah, also had plenty to eat and drink.\n\tBut he was just and
        right in all his dealings.\n\tThat is why God blessed him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He gave justice and help to the poor and needy,\n\tand everything
        went well for him.\n\tIsn\u2019t that what it means to know me?\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you! You have eyes only for greed and dishonesty!\n\tYou
        murder the innocent,\n\toppress the poor, and reign ruthlessly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about
        Jehoiakim, son of King Josiah:\n\t\u201CThe people will not mourn for him,
        crying to one another,\n\t\u2018Alas, my brother! Alas, my sister!\u2019\n\tHis
        subjects will not mourn for him, crying,\n\t\u2018Alas, our master is dead!
        Alas, his splendor is gone!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will be buried like a dead donkey\u2014\n\tdragged out of Jerusalem
        and dumped outside the gates!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Weep for your allies in Lebanon.\n\tShout for them in Bashan.\n\tSearch
        for them in the regions east of the river.[COMMENT[0]]See, they are all destroyed.\n\tNot
        one is left to help you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: in Abarim.
    - title: 
      content: "I warned you when you were prosperous,\n\tbut you replied, \u2018Don\u2019t
        bother me.\u2019\n\tYou have been that way since childhood\u2014\n\tyou simply
        will not obey me!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And now the wind will blow away your allies.\n\tAll your friends
        will be taken away as captives.\n\tSurely then you will see your wickedness
        and be ashamed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It may be nice to live in a beautiful palace\n\tpaneled with wood
        from the cedars of Lebanon,\n\tbut soon you will groan with pangs of anguish\u2014\n\tanguish
        like that of a woman in labor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message for Jehoiachin
      content: "\u201CAs surely as I live,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201CI will abandon you, Jehoiachin[COMMENT[0]] son of Jehoiakim, king of
        Judah. Even if you were the signet ring on my right hand, I would pull you
        off. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Coniah, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehoiachin; also in 22:28.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I will hand you over to those who seek to kill you, those you so
        desperately fear\u2014to King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[0]] of Babylon and the
        mighty Babylonian[COMMENT[1]] army. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:25a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
          body: 
      - number: '22:25b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldean.
    - title: 
      content: 'I will expel you and your mother from this land, and you will die
        in a foreign country, not in your native land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will never again return to the land you yearn for.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy is this man Jehoiachin like a discarded, broken jar?\n\tWhy
        are he and his children to be exiled to a foreign land?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O earth, earth, earth!\n\tListen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u2018Let the
        record show that this man Jehoiachin was childless.\n\tHe is a failure,\n\tfor
        none of his children will succeed him on the throne of David\n\tto rule over
        Judah.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Righteous Descendant
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits the leaders of my people\u2014the shepherds
        of my sheep\u2014for they have destroyed and scattered the very ones they
        were expected to care for,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the
        God of Israel, says to these shepherds: \u201CInstead of caring for my flock
        and leading them to safety, you have deserted them and driven them to destruction.
        Now I will pour out judgment on you for the evil you have done to them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I will gather together the remnant of my flock from the countries
        where I have driven them. I will bring them back to their own sheepfold,
        and they will be fruitful and increase in number. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I will appoint responsible shepherds who will care for them,
        and they will never be afraid again. Not a single one will be lost or missing.
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor the time is coming,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cwhen
        I will raise up a righteous descendant[COMMENT[0]]from King David\u2019s
        line.\n\tHe will be a King who rules with wisdom.\n\tHe will do what is just
        and right throughout the land.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: a righteous branch.
    - title: 
      content: "And this will be his name:\n\t\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        Is Our Righteousness.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]In that day Judah will be saved,\n\tand
        Israel will live in safety.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Yahweh Tsidqenu.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cwhen people are taking an oath, they will no longer say, \u2018As surely
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, who rescued the people of Israel
        from the land of Egypt.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, they will say, \u2018As surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, who brought the people of Israel back to their own land from the land
        of the north and from all the countries to which he had exiled them.\u2019
        Then they will live in their own land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Judgment on False Prophets
      content: "My heart is broken because of the false prophets,\n\tand my bones
        tremble.\n\tI stagger like a drunkard,\n\tlike someone overcome by wine,\n\tbecause
        of the holy words\n\tthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken against them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the land is full of adultery,\n\tand it lies under a curse.\n\tThe
        land itself is in mourning\u2014\n\tits wilderness pastures are dried up.\n\tFor
        they all do evil\n\tand abuse what power they have.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEven the priests and prophets\n\tare ungodly, wicked men.\n\tI
        have seen their despicable acts\n\tright here in my own Temple,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, the paths they take\n\twill become slippery.\n\tThey
        will be chased through the dark,\n\tand there they will fall.\n\tFor I will
        bring disaster upon them\n\tat the time fixed for their punishment.\n\tI,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI saw that the prophets of Samaria were terribly evil,\n\tfor
        they prophesied in the name of Baal\n\tand led my people of Israel into sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now I see that the prophets of Jerusalem are even worse!\n\tThey
        commit adultery and love dishonesty.\n\tThey encourage those who are doing
        evil\n\tso that no one turns away from their sins.\n\tThese prophets are
        as wicked\n\tas the people of Sodom and Gomorrah once were.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says concerning the prophets:\n\t\u201CI will feed them with bitterness\n\tand
        give them poison to drink.\n\tFor it is because of Jerusalem\u2019s prophets\n\tthat
        wickedness has filled this land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says to his people:\n\t\u201CDo not listen to these prophets when they prophesy
        to you,\n\tfilling you with futile hopes.\n\tThey are making up everything
        they say.\n\tThey do not speak for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They keep saying to those who despise my word,\n\t\u2018Don\u2019t
        worry! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says you will have peace!\u2019\n\tAnd
        to those who stubbornly follow their own desires,\n\tthey say, \u2018No harm
        will come your way!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave any of these prophets been in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        presence\n\tto hear what he is really saying?\n\tHas even one of them cared
        enough to listen?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s anger bursts out
        like a storm,\n\ta whirlwind that swirls down on the heads of the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not diminish\n\tuntil
        it has finished all he has planned.\n\tIn the days to come\n\tyou will understand
        all this very clearly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have not sent these prophets,\n\tyet they run around claiming
        to speak for me.\n\tI have given them no message,\n\tyet they go on prophesying.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If they had stood before me and listened to me,\n\tthey would have
        spoken my words,\n\tand they would have turned my people\n\tfrom their evil
        ways and deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Am I a God who is only close at hand?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CNo,
        I am far away at the same time.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can anyone hide from me in a secret place?\n\tAm I not everywhere
        in all the heavens and earth?\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have heard these prophets say, \u2018Listen to the dream
        I had from God last night.\u2019 And then they proceed to tell lies in my
        name. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How long will this go on? If they are prophets, they are prophets
        of deceit, inventing everything they say. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By telling these false dreams, they are trying to get my people to
        forget me, just as their ancestors did by worshiping the idols of Baal.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLet these false prophets tell their dreams,\n\tbut let my true
        messengers faithfully proclaim my every word.\n\tThere is a difference between
        straw and grain!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does not my word burn like fire?\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CIs
        it not like a mighty hammer\n\tthat smashes a rock to pieces?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201CI am against these prophets who steal messages from each other and
        claim they are from me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am against these smooth-tongued prophets who say, \u2018This prophecy
        is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am against these false prophets. Their imaginary dreams are flagrant
        lies that lead my people into sin. I did not send or appoint them, and they
        have no message at all for my people. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: False Prophecies and False Prophets
      content: "\u201CSuppose one of the people or one of the prophets or priests
        asks you, \u2018What prophecy has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> burdened
        you with now?\u2019 You must reply, \u2018You are the burden![COMMENT[0]]
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says he will abandon you!\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:33 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version and Latin Vulgate; Hebrew reads '
          body: What burden?
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf any prophet, priest, or anyone else says, \u2018I have a
        prophecy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\u2019 I will punish that
        person along with his entire family. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You should keep asking each other, \u2018What is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        answer?\u2019 or \u2018What is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saying?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But stop using this phrase, \u2018prophecy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u2019
        For people are using it to give authority to their own ideas, turning upside
        down the words of our God, the living God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what you should say to the prophets: \u2018What is
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s answer?\u2019 or \u2018What is
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saying?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But suppose they respond, \u2018This is a prophecy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\u2019
        Then you should say, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        Because you have used this phrase, \u201Cprophecy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\u201D
        even though I warned you not to use it, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will forget you completely.[COMMENT[0]] I will expel you from my
        presence, along with this city that I gave to you and your ancestors. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:39 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version read '
          body: I will surely lift you up.
    - title: 
      content: "And I will make you an object of ridicule, and your name will be
        infamous throughout the ages.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Good and Bad Figs
      content: "After King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[0]] of Babylon exiled Jehoiachin[COMMENT[1]]
        son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, to Babylon along with the officials of Judah
        and all the craftsmen and artisans, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave
        me this vision. I saw two baskets of figs placed in front of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Temple in Jerusalem. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
          body: 
      - number: '24:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jeconiah, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'One basket was filled with fresh, ripe figs, while the other was
        filled with bad figs that were too rotten to eat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CWhat do you
        see, Jeremiah?\u201D\n\tI replied, \u201CFigs, some very good and some very
        bad, too rotten to eat.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me this message: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of
        Israel, says: The good figs represent the exiles I sent from Judah to the
        land of the Babylonians.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldeans.
    - title: 
      content: 'I will watch over and care for them, and I will bring them back here
        again. I will build them up and not tear them down. I will plant them and
        not uproot them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give them hearts that recognize me as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        They will be my people, and I will be their God, for they will return to
        me wholeheartedly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut the bad figs,\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said,
        \u201Crepresent King Zedekiah of Judah, his officials, all the people left
        in Jerusalem, and those who live in Egypt. I will treat them like bad figs,
        too rotten to eat. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will make them an object of horror and a symbol of evil to every
        nation on earth. They will be disgraced and mocked, taunted and cursed, wherever
        I scatter them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will send war, famine, and disease until they have vanished
        from the land of Israel, which I gave to them and their ancestors.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Seventy Years of Captivity
      content: "This message for all the people of Judah came to Jeremiah from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> during the fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign
        over Judah.[COMMENT[0]] This was the year when King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[1]]
        of Babylon began his reign.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: "The fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign and the accession year of
            Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign was 605 "
          body: 
      - number: '25:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar; also in 25:9.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Jeremiah the prophet said to all the people in Judah and Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor the past twenty-three years\u2014from the thirteenth year
        of the reign of Josiah son of Amon,[COMMENT[0]] king of Judah, until now\u2014the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has been giving me his messages. I have faithfully
        passed them on to you, but you have not listened.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: "The thirteenth year of Josiah\u2019s reign was 627 "
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAgain and again the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent you
        his servants, the prophets, but you have not listened or even paid attention. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Each time the message was this: \u2018Turn from the evil road you
        are traveling and from the evil things you are doing. Only then will I let
        you live in this land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave to you and
        your ancestors forever. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not provoke my anger by worshiping idols you made with your own
        hands. Then I will not harm you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you would not listen to me,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        \u201CYou made me furious by worshiping idols you made with your own hands,
        bringing on yourselves all the disasters you now suffer. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies says:
        Because you have not listened to me, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will gather together all the armies of the north under King Nebuchadnezzar
        of Babylon, whom I have appointed as my deputy. I will bring them all against
        this land and its people and against the surrounding nations. I will completely
        destroy[COMMENT[0]] you and make you an object of horror and contempt and
        a ruin forever. '
      comments:
      - number: '25:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of things
            or people to the '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'I will take away your happy singing and laughter. The joyful voices
        of bridegrooms and brides will no longer be heard. Your millstones will fall
        silent, and the lights in your homes will go out. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This entire land will become a desolate wasteland. Israel and her
        neighboring lands will serve the king of Babylon for seventy years.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen, after the seventy years of captivity are over, I will
        punish the king of Babylon and his people for their sins,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u201CI will make the country of the Babylonians[COMMENT[0]]
        a wasteland forever. "
      comments:
      - number: '25:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldeans.
    - title: 
      content: "I will bring upon them all the terrors I have promised in this book\u2014all
        the penalties announced by Jeremiah against the nations. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Many nations and great kings will enslave the Babylonians, just as
        they enslaved my people. I will punish them in proportion to the suffering
        they cause my people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Anger"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of Israel,
        said to me: \u201CTake from my hand this cup filled to the brim with my anger,
        and make all the nations to whom I send you drink from it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they drink from it, they will stagger, crazed by the warfare
        I will send against them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I took the cup of anger from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        made all the nations drink from it\u2014every nation to which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I went to Jerusalem and the other towns of Judah, and their kings
        and officials drank from the cup. From that day until this, they have been
        a desolate ruin, an object of horror, contempt, and cursing. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I gave the cup to Pharaoh, king of Egypt, his attendants, his officials,
        and all his people, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'along with all the foreigners living in that land. I also gave it
        to all the kings of the land of Uz and the kings of the Philistine cities
        of Ashkelon, Gaza, Ekron, and what remains of Ashdod. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I gave the cup to the nations of Edom, Moab, and Ammon, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the kings of Tyre and Sidon, and the kings of the regions across
        the sea. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I gave it to Dedan, Tema, and Buz, and to the people who live in
        distant places.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:23 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: who clip the corners of their hair.
    - title: 
      content: 'I gave it to the kings of Arabia, the kings of the nomadic tribes
        of the desert, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and to the kings of Zimri, Elam, and Media. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I gave it to the kings of the northern countries, far and near,
        one after the other\u2014all the kingdoms of the world. And finally, the
        king of Babylon[COMMENT[0]] himself drank from the cup of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        anger.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:26 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'of Sheshach, '
        - ft: a code name for Babylon.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CNow tell them,
        \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: Drink from this cup of my anger. Get drunk and vomit;
        fall to rise no more, for I am sending terrible wars against you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if they refuse to accept the cup, tell them, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says: You have no choice but to drink from it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have begun to punish Jerusalem, the city that bears my name. Now
        should I let you go unpunished? No, you will not escape disaster. I will
        call for war against all the nations of the earth. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, have spoken!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow prophesy all these things, and say to them,\n\t\u201C\u2018The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will roar against his own land\n\tfrom his holy
        dwelling in heaven.\n\tHe will shout like those who tread grapes;\n\the will
        shout against everyone on earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His cry of judgment will reach the ends of the earth,\n\tfor the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring his case against all the nations.\n\tHe
        will judge all the people of the earth,\n\tslaughtering the wicked with the
        sword.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\n\t\u201CLook! Disaster will fall upon nation after nation!\n\tA great
        whirlwind of fury is rising\n\tfrom the most distant corners of the earth!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day those the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has slaughtered
        will fill the earth from one end to the other. No one will mourn for them
        or gather up their bodies to bury them. They will be scattered on the ground
        like manure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Weep and moan, you evil shepherds!\n\tRoll in the dust, you leaders
        of the flock!\n\tThe time of your slaughter has arrived;\n\tyou will fall
        and shatter like a fragile vase.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will find no place to hide;\n\tthere will be no way to escape.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to the frantic cries of the shepherds.\n\tThe leaders of the
        flock are wailing in despair,\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is ruining
        their pastures.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Peaceful meadows will be turned into a wasteland\n\tby the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        fierce anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He has left his den like a strong lion seeking its prey,\n\tand their
        land will be made desolate\n\tby the sword[COMMENT[0]] of the enemy\n\tand
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s fierce anger."
      comments:
      - number: '25:38 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version; Masoretic Text reads '
          body: by the anger.
  - verses:
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Escape from Death"
      content: 'This message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        early in the reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah,[COMMENT[0]] king of Judah. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: "The first year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign was 608 "
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Stand in
        the courtyard in front of the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        and make an announcement to the people who have come there to worship from
        all over Judah. Give them my entire message; include every word. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Perhaps they will listen and turn from their evil ways. Then I will
        change my mind about the disaster I am ready to pour out on them because
        of their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSay to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: If you will not listen to me and obey my word I have given you, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and if you will not listen to my servants, the prophets\u2014for
        I sent them again and again to warn you, but you would not listen to them\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then I will destroy this Temple as I destroyed Shiloh, the place
        where the Tabernacle was located. And I will make Jerusalem an object of
        cursing in every nation on earth.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The priests, the prophets, and all the people listened to Jeremiah
        as he spoke in front of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Temple. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when Jeremiah had finished his message, saying everything the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had told him to say, the priests and prophets
        and all the people at the Temple mobbed him. \u201CKill him!\u201D they shouted. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat right do you have to prophesy in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        name that this Temple will be destroyed like Shiloh? What do you mean, saying
        that Jerusalem will be destroyed and left with no inhabitants?\u201D And
        all the people threatened him as he stood in front of the Temple.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the officials of Judah heard what was happening, they rushed
        over from the palace and sat down at the New Gate of the Temple to hold court. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The priests and prophets presented their accusations to the officials
        and the people. \u201CThis man should die!\u201D they said. \u201CYou have
        heard with your own ears what a traitor he is, for he has prophesied against
        this city.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jeremiah spoke to the officials and the people in his own defense.
        \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent me to prophesy against this Temple
        and this city,\u201D he said. \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave
        me every word that I have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if you stop your sinning and begin to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, he will change his mind about this disaster that he has announced
        against you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As for me, I am in your hands\u2014do with me as you think best. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you kill me, rest assured that you will be killing an innocent
        man! The responsibility for such a deed will lie on you, on this city, and
        on every person living in it. For it is absolutely true that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent me to speak every word you have heard.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the officials and the people said to the priests and prophets,
        \u201CThis man does not deserve the death sentence, for he has spoken to
        us in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then some of the wise old men stood and spoke to all the people assembled
        there. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They said, \u201CRemember when Micah of Moresheth prophesied during
        the reign of King Hezekiah of Judah. He told the people of Judah,\n\t\u2018This
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies says:\n\tMount
        Zion will be plowed like an open field;\n\tJerusalem will be reduced to ruins!\n\tA
        thicket will grow on the heights\n\twhere the Temple now stands.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: Mic 3:12.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "But did King Hezekiah and the people kill him for saying this? No,
        they turned from their sins and worshiped the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        They begged him for mercy. Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> changed his
        mind about the terrible disaster he had pronounced against them. So we are
        about to do ourselves great harm.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At this time Uriah son of Shemaiah from Kiriath-jearim was also prophesying
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. And he predicted the same terrible
        disaster against the city and nation as Jeremiah did. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When King Jehoiakim and the army officers and officials heard what
        he was saying, the king sent someone to kill him. But Uriah heard about the
        plan and escaped in fear to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then King Jehoiakim sent Elnathan son of Acbor to Egypt along with
        several other men to capture Uriah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They took him prisoner and brought him back to King Jehoiakim. The
        king then killed Uriah with a sword and had him buried in an unmarked grave.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Nevertheless, Ahikam son of Shaphan stood up for Jeremiah and persuaded
        the court not to turn him over to the mob to be killed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jeremiah Wears an Ox Yoke
      content: 'This message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        early in the reign of Zedekiah[COMMENT[0]] son of Josiah, king of Judah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Syriac version (see also 27:3, 12);
            most Hebrew manuscripts read '
          body: Jehoiakim.
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CMake
        a yoke, and fasten it on your neck with leather straps. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then send messages to the kings of Edom, Moab, Ammon, Tyre, and Sidon
        through their ambassadors who have come to see King Zedekiah in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Give them this message for their masters: \u2018This is what the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With my great strength and powerful arm I made the earth and all
        its people and every animal. I can give these things of mine to anyone I
        choose. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now I will give your countries to King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon,
        who is my servant. I have put everything, even the wild animals, under his
        control. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the nations will serve him, his son, and his grandson until his
        time is up. Then many nations and great kings will conquer and rule over
        Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So you must submit to Babylon\u2019s king and serve him; put your
        neck under Babylon\u2019s yoke! I will punish any nation that refuses to
        be his slave, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. I will send war,
        famine, and disease upon that nation until Babylon has conquered it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Do not listen to your false prophets, fortune-tellers,
        interpreters of dreams, mediums, and sorcerers who say, \u201CThe king of
        Babylon will not conquer you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are all liars, and their lies will lead to your being driven
        out of your land. I will drive you out and send you far away to die. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people of any nation that submits to the king of Babylon
        will be allowed to stay in their own country to farm the land as usual. I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I repeated this same message to King Zedekiah of Judah. \u201CIf
        you want to live, submit to the yoke of the king of Babylon and his people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why do you insist on dying\u2014you and your people? Why should you
        choose war, famine, and disease, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        bring against every nation that refuses to submit to Babylon\u2019s king? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not listen to the false prophets who keep telling you, \u2018The
        king of Babylon will not conquer you.\u2019 They are liars. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018I have not
        sent these prophets! They are telling you lies in my name, so I will drive
        you from this land. You will all die\u2014you and all these prophets, too.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I spoke to the priests and the people and said, \u201CThis is
        what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018Do not listen to your prophets
        who claim that soon the gold articles taken from my Temple will be returned
        from Babylon. It is all a lie! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not listen to them. Surrender to the king of Babylon, and you
        will live. Why should this whole city be destroyed? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If they really are prophets and speak the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        messages, let them pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies. Let them pray that the articles remaining in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Temple and in the king\u2019s palace and in the palaces of Jerusalem will
        not be carried away to Babylon!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        has spoken about the pillars in front of the Temple, the great bronze basin
        called the Sea, the water carts, and all the other ceremonial articles. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon left them here when he exiled Jehoiachin[COMMENT[0]]
        son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, to Babylon, along with all the other nobles
        of Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jeconiah, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says about the precious things still in the Temple,
        in the palace of Judah\u2019s king, and in Jerusalem: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018They will all be carried away to Babylon and will stay there
        until I send for them,\u2019 says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u2018Then
        I will bring them back to Jerusalem again.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jeremiah Condemns Hananiah
      content: "One day in late summer[COMMENT[0]] of that same year\u2014the fourth
        year of the reign of Zedekiah, king of Judah\u2014Hananiah son of Azzur,
        a prophet from Gibeon, addressed me publicly in the Temple while all the
        priests and people listened. He said, "
      comments:
      - number: '28:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'In the fifth month, '
        - ft: "of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar. The fifth month in the fourth
            year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign occurred within the months of August and
            September 593 "
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018I will remove the yoke of the king
        of Babylon from your necks. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Within two years I will bring back all the Temple treasures that
        King Nebuchadnezzar carried off to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will bring back Jehoiachin[COMMENT[0]] son of Jehoiakim, king
        of Judah, and all the other captives that were taken to Babylon. I will surely
        break the yoke that the king of Babylon has put on your necks. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jeconiah, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Jeremiah responded to Hananiah as they stood in front of all the
        priests and people at the Temple. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said, \u201CAmen! May your prophecies come true! I hope the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        does everything you say. I hope he does bring back from Babylon the treasures
        of this Temple and all the captives. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But listen now to the solemn words I speak to you in the presence
        of all these people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The ancient prophets who preceded you and me spoke against many nations,
        always warning of war, disaster, and disease. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So a prophet who predicts peace must show he is right. Only when
        his predictions come true can we know that he is really from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Hananiah the prophet took the yoke off Jeremiah\u2019s neck
        and broke it in pieces. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And Hananiah said again to the crowd that had gathered, \u201CThis
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018Just as this yoke has
        been broken, within two years I will break the yoke of oppression from all
        the nations now subject to King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon.\u2019\u201D With
        that, Jeremiah left the Temple area.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Soon after this confrontation with Hananiah, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo and tell Hananiah, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: You have broken a wooden yoke, but you have replaced it with a yoke
        of iron. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God
        of Israel, says: I have put a yoke of iron on the necks of all these nations,
        forcing them into slavery under King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon. I have put
        everything, even the wild animals, under his control.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jeremiah the prophet said to Hananiah, \u201CListen, Hananiah!
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has not sent you, but the people believe
        your lies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018You
        must die. Your life will end this very year because you have rebelled against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Two months later[COMMENT[0]] the prophet Hananiah died.
      comments:
      - number: '28:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'In the seventh month of that same year. '
        - ft: See 28:1 and the note there.
          body: 
  - verses:
    - title: A Letter to the Exiles
      content: 'Jeremiah wrote a letter from Jerusalem to the elders, priests, prophets,
        and all the people who had been exiled to Babylon by King Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This was after King Jehoiachin,[COMMENT[0]] the queen mother, the
        court officials, the other officials of Judah, and all the craftsmen and
        artisans had been deported from Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '29:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jeconiah, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "He sent the letter with Elasah son of Shaphan and Gemariah son of
        Hilkiah when they went to Babylon as King Zedekiah\u2019s ambassadors to
        Nebuchadnezzar. This is what Jeremiah\u2019s letter said:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says to all the captives he has exiled to Babylon from
        Jerusalem: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBuild homes, and plan to stay. Plant gardens, and eat the food
        they produce. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Marry and have children. Then find spouses for them so that you may
        have many grandchildren. Multiply! Do not dwindle away! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And work for the peace and prosperity of the city where I sent you
        into exile. Pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for it, for its welfare
        will determine your welfare.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u201CDo not let your prophets and fortune-tellers
        who are with you in the land of Babylon trick you. Do not listen to their
        dreams, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "because they are telling you lies in my name. I have not sent them,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CYou will
        be in Babylon for seventy years. But then I will come and do for you all
        the good things I have promised, and I will bring you home again. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I know the plans I have for you,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        \u201CThey are plans for good and not for disaster, to give you a future
        and a hope. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In those days when you pray, I will listen. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you look for me wholeheartedly, you will find me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will be found by you,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        \u201CI will end your captivity and restore your fortunes. I will gather
        you out of the nations where I sent you and will bring you home again to
        your own land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You claim that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has raised up prophets
        for you in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about the king
        who sits on David\u2019s throne and all those still living here in Jerusalem\u2014your
        relatives who were not exiled to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says: \u201CI will send war, famine, and disease upon them and make them
        like bad figs, too rotten to eat. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, I will pursue them with war, famine, and disease, and I will
        scatter them around the world. In every nation where I send them, I will
        make them an object of damnation, horror, contempt, and mockery. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they refuse to listen to me, though I have spoken to them repeatedly
        through the prophets I sent. And you who are in exile have not listened either,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        all you captives there in Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says about your prophets\u2014Ahab son of Kolaiah and
        Zedekiah son of Maaseiah\u2014who are telling you lies in my name: \u201CI
        will turn them over to Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[0]] for execution before your
        eyes. "
      comments:
      - number: '29:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Their terrible fate will become proverbial, so that the Judean exiles
        will curse someone by saying, \u2018May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> make
        you like Zedekiah and Ahab, whom the king of Babylon burned alive!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For these men have done terrible things among my people. They have
        committed adultery with their neighbors\u2019 wives and have lied in my name,
        saying things I did not command. I am a witness to this. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message for Shemaiah
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent this message to Shemaiah the
        Nehelamite in Babylon: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: You wrote a letter on your own authority
        to Zephaniah son of Maaseiah, the priest, and you sent copies to the other
        priests and people in Jerusalem. You wrote to Zephaniah,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has appointed you to replace
        Jehoiada as the priest in charge of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        You are responsible to put into stocks and neck irons any crazy man who claims
        to be a prophet. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So why have you done nothing to stop Jeremiah from Anathoth, who
        pretends to be a prophet among you? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jeremiah sent a letter here to Babylon, predicting that our captivity
        will be a long one. He said, \u2018Build homes, and plan to stay. Plant gardens,
        and eat the food they produce.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when Zephaniah the priest received Shemaiah\u2019s letter, he
        took it to Jeremiah and read it to him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSend an open letter to all the exiles in Babylon. Tell them,
        \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says concerning Shemaiah
        the Nehelamite: Since he has prophesied to you when I did not send him and
        has tricked you into believing his lies, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will punish him and his family. None of his descendants will see
        the good things I will do for my people, for he has incited you to rebel
        against me. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Promises of Deliverance
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of
        Israel, says: Write down for the record everything I have said to you, Jeremiah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the time is coming when I will restore the fortunes of my people
        of Israel and Judah. I will bring them home to this land that I gave to their
        ancestors, and they will possess it again. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is the message the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave concerning
        Israel and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CI hear
        cries of fear;\n\tthere is terror and no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now let me ask you a question:\n\tDo men give birth to babies?\n\tThen
        why do they stand there, ashen-faced,\n\thands pressed against their sides\n\tlike
        a woman in labor?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In all history there has never been such a time of terror.\n\tIt
        will be a time of trouble for my people Israel.[COMMENT[0]]Yet in the end
        they will be saved!  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jacob; '
        - ft: also in 30:10b, 18. See note on 5:20.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "For in that day,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        Heaven\u2019s Armies,\n\t\u201CI will break the yoke from their necks\n\tand
        snap their chains.\n\tForeigners will no longer be their masters.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For my people will serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God\n\tand
        their king descended from David\u2014\n\tthe king I will raise up for them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo do not be afraid, Jacob, my servant;\n\tdo not be dismayed,
        Israel,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CFor I
        will bring you home again from distant lands,\n\tand your children will return
        from their exile.\n\tIsrael will return to a life of peace and quiet,\n\tand
        no one will terrorize them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I am with you and will save you,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CI
        will completely destroy the nations where I have scattered you,\n\tbut I
        will not completely destroy you.\n\tI will discipline you, but with justice;\n\tI
        cannot let you go unpunished.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CYour
        injury is incurable\u2014\n\ta terrible wound.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There is no one to help you\n\tor to bind up your injury.\n\tNo medicine
        can heal you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All your lovers\u2014your allies\u2014have left you\n\tand do not
        care about you anymore.\n\tI have wounded you cruelly,\n\tas though I were
        your enemy.\n\tFor your sins are many,\n\tand your guilt is great.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why do you protest your punishment\u2014\n\tthis wound that has no
        cure?\n\tI have had to punish you\n\tbecause your sins are many\n\tand your
        guilt is great.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut all who devour you will be devoured,\n\tand all your enemies
        will be sent into exile.\n\tAll who plunder you will be plundered,\n\tand
        all who attack you will be attacked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give you back your health\n\tand heal your wounds,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CFor you are called an outcast\u2014\n\t\u2018Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]]
        for whom no one cares.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CWhen
        I bring Israel home again from captivity\n\tand restore their fortunes,\n\tJerusalem
        will be rebuilt on its ruins,\n\tand the palace reconstructed as before.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There will be joy and songs of thanksgiving,\n\tand I will multiply
        my people, not diminish them;\n\tI will honor them, not despise them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their children will prosper as they did long ago.\n\tI will establish
        them as a nation before me,\n\tand I will punish anyone who hurts them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will have their own ruler again,\n\tand he will come from their
        own people.\n\tI will invite him to approach me,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cfor
        who would dare to come unless invited?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be my people,\n\tand I will be your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s anger bursts out
        like a storm,\n\ta driving wind that swirls down on the heads of the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not diminish\n\tuntil
        it has finished all he has planned.\n\tIn the days to come\n\tyou will understand
        all this."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Hope for Restoration
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201CI will be the God of all the families of Israel, and they will be my
        people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThose
        who survive the coming destruction\n\twill find blessings even in the barren
        land,\n\tfor I will give rest to the people of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Long ago the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Israel:\n\t\u201CI
        have loved you, my people, with an everlasting love.\n\tWith unfailing love
        I have drawn you to myself.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will rebuild you, my virgin Israel.\n\tYou will again be happy\n\tand
        dance merrily with your tambourines.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Again you will plant your vineyards on the mountains of Samaria\n\tand
        eat from your own gardens there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The day will come when watchmen will shout\n\tfrom the hill country
        of Ephraim,\n\t\u2018Come, let us go up to Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]]to worship
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Zion; '
        - ft: also in 31:12.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CSing
        with joy for Israel.[COMMENT[0]]Shout for the greatest of nations!\n\tShout
        out with praise and joy:\n\t\u2018Save your people, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tthe
        remnant of Israel!\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jacob; '
        - ft: also in 31:11. See note on 5:20.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "For I will bring them from the north\n\tand from the distant corners
        of the earth.\n\tI will not forget the blind and lame,\n\tthe expectant mothers
        and women in labor.\n\tA great company will return!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Tears of joy will stream down their faces,\n\tand I will lead them
        home with great care.\n\tThey will walk beside quiet streams\n\tand on smooth
        paths where they will not stumble.\n\tFor I am Israel\u2019s father,\n\tand
        Ephraim is my oldest child.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tyou
        nations of the world;\n\tproclaim it in distant coastlands:\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        who scattered his people,\n\twill gather them and watch over them\n\tas a
        shepherd does his flock.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has redeemed Israel\n\tfrom those
        too strong for them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will come home and sing songs of joy on the heights of Jerusalem.\n\tThey
        will be radiant because of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s good
        gifts\u2014\n\tthe abundant crops of grain, new wine, and olive oil,\n\tand
        the healthy flocks and herds.\n\tTheir life will be like a watered garden,\n\tand
        all their sorrows will be gone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The young women will dance for joy,\n\tand the men\u2014old and young\u2014will
        join in the celebration.\n\tI will turn their mourning into joy.\n\tI will
        comfort them and exchange their sorrow for rejoicing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The priests will enjoy abundance,\n\tand my people will feast on
        my good gifts.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Rachel\u2019s Sadness Turns to Joy"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CA cry
        is heard in Ramah\u2014\n\tdeep anguish and bitter weeping.\n\tRachel weeps
        for her children,\n\trefusing to be comforted\u2014\n\tfor her children are
        gone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CDo
        not weep any longer,\n\tfor I will reward you,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CYour
        children will come back to you\n\tfrom the distant land of the enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There is hope for your future,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CYour
        children will come again to their own land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have heard Israel[COMMENT[0]] saying,\n\t\u2018You disciplined
        me severely,\n\tlike a calf that needs training for the yoke.\n\tTurn me
        again to you and restore me,\n\tfor you alone are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God.  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Ephraim, '
        - ft: referring to the northern kingdom of Israel; also in 31:20.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I turned away from God,\n\tbut then I was sorry.\n\tI kicked myself
        for my stupidity!\n\tI was thoroughly ashamed of all I did in my younger
        days.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIs not Israel still my son,\n\tmy darling child?\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CI often have to punish him,\n\tbut
        I still love him.\n\tThat\u2019s why I long for him\n\tand surely will have
        mercy on him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Set up road signs;\n\tput up guideposts.\n\tMark well the path\n\tby
        which you came.\n\tCome back again, my virgin Israel;\n\treturn to your towns
        here.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How long will you wander,\n\tmy wayward daughter?\n\tFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will cause something new to happen\u2014\n\tIsrael will embrace her God.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:22 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: a woman will surround a man.
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u201CWhen I bring them back from captivity, the
        people of Judah and its towns will again say, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        bless you, O righteous home, O holy mountain!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Townspeople and farmers and shepherds alike will live together in
        peace and happiness. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I have given rest to the weary and joy to the sorrowing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At this, I woke up and looked around. My sleep had been very sweet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe day is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cwhen I will greatly increase the human population and the number of
        animals here in Israel and Judah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the past I deliberately uprooted and tore down this nation. I
        overthrew it, destroyed it, and brought disaster upon it. But in the future
        I will just as deliberately plant it and build it up. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe people will no longer quote this proverb:\n\t\u2018The
        parents have eaten sour grapes,\n\tbut their children\u2019s mouths pucker
        at the taste.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All people will die for their own sins\u2014those who eat the sour
        grapes will be the ones whose mouths will pucker.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe day is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cwhen I will make a new covenant with the people of Israel and Judah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This covenant will not be like the one I made with their ancestors
        when I took them by the hand and brought them out of the land of Egypt. They
        broke that covenant, though I loved them as a husband loves his wife,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut this is the new covenant I will make with the people of
        Israel after those days,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        \u201CI will put my instructions deep within them, and I will write them
        on their hearts. I will be their God, and they will be my people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they will not need to teach their neighbors, nor will they need
        to teach their relatives, saying, \u2018You should know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u2019
        For everyone, from the least to the greatest, will know me already,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u201CAnd I will forgive their
        wickedness, and I will never again remember their sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who provides the sun to light
        the day\n\tand the moon and stars to light the night,\n\tand who stirs the
        sea into roaring waves.\n\tHis name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        Heaven\u2019s Armies,\n\tand this is what he says:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am as likely to reject my people Israel\n\tas I am to abolish
        the laws of nature!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CJust
        as the heavens cannot be measured\n\tand the foundations of the earth cannot
        be explored,\n\tso I will not consider casting them away\n\tfor the evil
        they have done.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe day is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cwhen all Jerusalem will be rebuilt for me, from the Tower of Hananel
        to the Corner Gate. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A measuring line will be stretched out over the hill of Gareb and
        across to Goah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the entire area\u2014including the graveyard and ash dump in
        the valley, and all the fields out to the Kidron Valley on the east as far
        as the Horse Gate\u2014will be holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        The city will never again be captured or destroyed.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Land Purchase"
      content: 'The following message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the tenth year of the reign of Zedekiah,[COMMENT[0]] king of Judah. This
        was also the eighteenth year of the reign of King Nebuchadnezzar.[COMMENT[1]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: "The tenth year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign and the eighteenth year of
            Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign was 587 "
          body: 
      - number: '32:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar; also in 32:28.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Jerusalem was then under siege from the Babylonian army, and Jeremiah
        was imprisoned in the courtyard of the guard in the royal palace. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "King Zedekiah had put him there, asking why he kept giving this prophecy:
        \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018I am about
        to hand this city over to the king of Babylon, and he will take it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'King Zedekiah will be captured by the Babylonians[COMMENT[0]] and
        taken to meet the king of Babylon face to face. '
      comments:
      - number: '32:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Chaldeans; '
        - ft: also in 32:5, 24, 25, 28, 29, 43.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "He will take Zedekiah to Babylon, and I will deal with him there,\u2019
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u2018If you fight against the
        Babylonians, you will never succeed.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent me a message. He
        said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYour cousin Hanamel son of Shallum will come and say to you,
        \u2018Buy my field at Anathoth. By law you have the right to buy it before
        it is offered to anyone else.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had said he would,
        my cousin Hanamel came and visited me in the prison. He said, \u201CPlease
        buy my field at Anathoth in the land of Benjamin. By law you have the right
        to buy it before it is offered to anyone else, so buy it for yourself.\u201D
        Then I knew that the message I had heard was from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I bought the field at Anathoth, paying Hanamel seventeen pieces[COMMENT[0]]
        of silver for it. '
      comments:
      - number: '32:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '17 shekels, '
        - ft: about 7 ounces or 194 grams in weight.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'I signed and sealed the deed of purchase before witnesses, weighed
        out the silver, and paid him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I took the sealed deed and an unsealed copy of the deed, which
        contained the terms and conditions of the purchase, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and I handed them to Baruch son of Neriah and grandson of Mahseiah.
        I did all this in the presence of my cousin Hanamel, the witnesses who had
        signed the deed, and all the men of Judah who were there in the courtyard
        of the guardhouse.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I said to Baruch as they all listened, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Take both this sealed deed and the
        unsealed copy, and put them into a pottery jar to preserve them for a long
        time.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Someday people will again own property
        here in this land and will buy and sell houses and vineyards and fields.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer"
      content: "Then after I had given the papers to Baruch, I prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t! You made the heavens
        and earth by your strong hand and powerful arm. Nothing is too hard for you! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You show unfailing love to thousands, but you also bring the consequences
        of one generation\u2019s sin upon the next. You are the great and powerful
        God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have all wisdom and do great and mighty miracles. You see the
        conduct of all people, and you give them what they deserve. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You performed miraculous signs and wonders in the land of Egypt\u2014things
        still remembered to this day! And you have continued to do great miracles
        in Israel and all around the world. You have made your name famous to this
        day.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou brought Israel out of Egypt with mighty signs and wonders,
        with a strong hand and powerful arm, and with overwhelming terror. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You gave the people of Israel this land that you had promised their
        ancestors long before\u2014a land flowing with milk and honey. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our ancestors came and conquered it and lived in it, but they refused
        to obey you or follow your word. They have not done anything you commanded.
        That is why you have sent this terrible disaster upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSee how the siege ramps have been built against the city walls!
        Through war, famine, and disease, the city will be handed over to the Babylonians,
        who will conquer it. Everything has happened just as you said. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And yet, O Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you have told
        me to buy the field\u2014paying good money for it before these witnesses\u2014even
        though the city will soon be handed over to the Babylonians.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "A Prediction of Jerusalem\u2019s Fall"
      content: "Then this message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of all the
        peoples of the world. Is anything too hard for me? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I will
        hand this city over to the Babylonians and to Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon,
        and he will capture it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Babylonians outside the walls will come in and set fire to the
        city. They will burn down all these houses where the people provoked my anger
        by burning incense to Baal on the rooftops and by pouring out liquid offerings
        to other gods. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Israel and Judah have done nothing but wrong since their earliest
        days. They have infuriated me with all their evil deeds,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFrom the time this city was built until now, it has done nothing
        but anger me, so I am determined to get rid of it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe sins of Israel and Judah\u2014the sins of the people of
        Jerusalem, the kings, the officials, the priests, and the prophets\u2014have
        stirred up my anger. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My people have turned their backs on me and have refused to return.
        Even though I diligently taught them, they would not receive instruction
        or obey. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have set up their abominable idols right in my own Temple, defiling
        it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have built pagan shrines to Baal in the valley of Ben-Hinnom,
        and there they sacrifice their sons and daughters to Molech. I have never
        commanded such a horrible deed; it never even crossed my mind to command
        such a thing. What an incredible evil, causing Judah to sin so greatly!  '
      comments: []
    - title: A Promise of Restoration
      content: "\u201CNow I want to say something more about this city. You have
        been saying, \u2018It will fall to the king of Babylon through war, famine,
        and disease.\u2019 But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of Israel, says: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will certainly bring my people back again from all the countries
        where I will scatter them in my fury. I will bring them back to this very
        city and let them live in peace and safety. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be my people, and I will be their God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I will give them one heart and one purpose: to worship me forever,
        for their own good and for the good of all their descendants. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I will make an everlasting covenant with them: I will never stop
        doing good for them. I will put a desire in their hearts to worship me, and
        they will never leave me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will find joy doing good for them and will faithfully and wholeheartedly
        replant them in this land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Just as
        I have brought all these calamities on them, so I will do all the good I
        have promised them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fields will again be bought and sold in this land about which you
        now say, \u2018It has been ravaged by the Babylonians, a desolate land where
        people and animals have all disappeared.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, fields will once again be bought and sold\u2014deeds signed
        and sealed and witnessed\u2014in the land of Benjamin and here in Jerusalem,
        in the towns of Judah and in the hill country, in the foothills of Judah[COMMENT[0]]
        and in the Negev, too. For someday I will restore prosperity to them. I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '32:44 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Shephelah.
  - verses:
    - title: Promises of Peace and Prosperity
      content: 'While Jeremiah was still confined in the courtyard of the guard,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave him this second message: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\u2014the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who made the earth, who formed and established
        it, whose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Ask me and I will tell you remarkable secrets you do not know about
        things to come. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of
        Israel, says: You have torn down the houses of this city and even the king\u2019s
        palace to get materials to strengthen the walls against the siege ramps and
        swords of the enemy. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You expect to fight the Babylonians,[COMMENT[0]] but the men of this
        city are already as good as dead, for I have determined to destroy them in
        my terrible anger. I have abandoned them because of all their wickedness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldeans.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNevertheless, the time will come when I will heal Jerusalem\u2019s
        wounds and give it prosperity and true peace. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will restore the fortunes of Judah and Israel and rebuild their
        towns. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will cleanse them of their sins against me and forgive all their
        sins of rebellion. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then this city will bring me joy, glory, and honor before all the
        nations of the earth! The people of the world will see all the good I do
        for my people, and they will tremble with awe at the peace and prosperity
        I provide for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: You have
        said, \u2018This is a desolate land where people and animals have all disappeared.\u2019
        Yet in the empty streets of Jerusalem and Judah\u2019s other towns, there
        will be heard once more "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the sounds of joy and laughter. The joyful voices of bridegrooms
        and brides will be heard again, along with the joyous songs of people bringing
        thanksgiving offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. They will
        sing,\n\t\u2018Give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good.\n\tHis faithful love
        endures forever!\u2019\n\tFor I will restore the prosperity of this land
        to what it was in the past, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: This land\u2014though it is now desolate and has no people and
        animals\u2014will once more have pastures where shepherds can lead their
        flocks. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Once again shepherds will count their flocks in the towns of the
        hill country, the foothills of Judah,[COMMENT[0]] the Negev, the land of
        Benjamin, the vicinity of Jerusalem, and all the towns of Judah. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Shephelah.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe day will come, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        when I will do for Israel and Judah all the good things I have promised them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn those days and at that time\n\tI will raise up a righteous
        descendant[COMMENT[0]] from King David\u2019s line.\n\tHe will do what is
        just and right throughout the land.  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: a righteous branch.
    - title: 
      content: "In that day Judah will be saved,\n\tand Jerusalem will live in safety.\n\tAnd
        this will be its name:\n\t\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Is Our Righteousness.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Yahweh Tsidqenu.
    - title: 
      content: 'For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: David will
        have a descendant sitting on the throne of Israel forever. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And there will always be Levitical priests to offer burnt offerings
        and grain offerings and sacrifices to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then this message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: If you can
        break my covenant with the day and the night so that one does not follow
        the other, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'only then will my covenant with my servant David be broken. Only
        then will he no longer have a descendant to reign on his throne. The same
        is true for my covenant with the Levitical priests who minister before me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And as the stars of the sky cannot be counted and the sand on the
        seashore cannot be measured, so I will multiply the descendants of my servant
        David and the Levites who minister before me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave you noticed what people are saying?\u2014\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        chose Judah and Israel and then abandoned them!\u2019 They are sneering and
        saying that Israel is not worthy to be counted as a nation. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I would no
        more reject my people than I would change my laws that govern night and day,
        earth and sky. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will never abandon the descendants of Jacob or David, my servant,
        or change the plan that David\u2019s descendants will rule the descendants
        of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. Instead, I will restore them to their land
        and have mercy on them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Warning for Zedekiah
      content: "King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[0]] of Babylon came with all the armies
        from the kingdoms he ruled, and he fought against Jerusalem and the towns
        of Judah. At that time this message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t: "
      comments:
      - number: '34:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo to King Zedekiah of Judah, and tell him, \u2018This is what
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of Israel, says: I am about
        to hand this city over to the king of Babylon, and he will burn it down. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will not escape his grasp but will be captured and taken to meet
        the king of Babylon face to face. Then you will be exiled to Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018But listen to this promise from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        O Zedekiah, king of Judah. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        You will not be killed in war "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but will die peacefully. People will burn incense in your memory,
        just as they did for your ancestors, the kings who preceded you. They will
        mourn for you, crying, \u201CAlas, our master is dead!\u201D This I have
        decreed, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Jeremiah the prophet delivered the message to King Zedekiah of
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At this time the Babylonian army was besieging Jerusalem, Lachish,
        and Azekah\u2014the only fortified cities of Judah not yet captured.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Freedom for Hebrew Slaves
      content: 'This message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        after King Zedekiah made a covenant with the people, proclaiming freedom
        for the slaves. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He had ordered all the people to free their Hebrew slaves\u2014both
        men and women. No one was to keep a fellow Judean in bondage. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The officials and all the people had obeyed the king\u2019s command, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but later they changed their minds. They took back the men and women
        they had freed, forcing them to be slaves again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them this message through
        Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of
        Israel, says: I made a covenant with your ancestors long ago when I rescued
        them from their slavery in Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I told them that every Hebrew slave must be freed after serving six
        years. But your ancestors paid no attention to me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Recently you repented and did what was right, following my command.
        You freed your slaves and made a solemn covenant with me in the Temple that
        bears my name. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now you have shrugged off your oath and defiled my name by taking
        back the men and women you had freed, forcing them to be slaves once again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        Since you have not obeyed me by setting your countrymen free, I will set
        you free to be destroyed by war, disease, and famine. You will be an object
        of horror to all the nations of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because you have broken the terms of our covenant, I will cut you
        apart just as you cut apart the calf when you walked between its halves to
        solemnize your vows. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, I will cut you apart, whether you are officials of Judah or
        Jerusalem, court officials, priests, or common people\u2014for you have broken
        your oath. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will give you to your enemies, and they will kill you. Your bodies
        will be food for the vultures and wild animals.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will hand over King Zedekiah of Judah and his officials to
        the army of the king of Babylon. And although they have left Jerusalem for
        a while, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will call the Babylonian armies back again. They will fight against
        this city and will capture it and burn it down. I will see to it that all
        the towns of Judah are destroyed, with no one living there.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Faithful Recabites
      content: 'This is the message the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Jeremiah
        when Jehoiakim son of Josiah was king of Judah: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo to the settlement where the families of the Recabites live,
        and invite them to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Temple. Take
        them into one of the inner rooms, and offer them some wine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I went to see Jaazaniah son of Jeremiah and grandson of Habazziniah
        and all his brothers and sons\u2014representing all the Recabite families. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I took them to the Temple, and we went into the room assigned to
        the sons of Hanan son of Igdaliah, a man of God. This room was located next
        to the one used by the Temple officials, directly above the room of Maaseiah
        son of Shallum, the Temple gatekeeper.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I set cups and jugs of wine before them and invited them to have
        a drink, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but they refused. \u201CNo,\u201D they said, \u201Cwe don\u2019t
        drink wine, because our ancestor Jehonadab[COMMENT[0]] son of Recab gave
        us this command: \u2018You and your descendants must never drink wine. "
      comments:
      - number: '35:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jonadab, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehonadab; also in 35:10, 19. See 2 Kgs 10:15.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "And do not build houses or plant crops or vineyards, but always live
        in tents. If you follow these commands, you will live long, good lives in
        the land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we have obeyed him in all these things. We have never had a drink
        of wine to this day, nor have our wives, our sons, or our daughters. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We haven\u2019t built houses or owned vineyards or farms or planted
        crops. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We have lived in tents and have fully obeyed all the commands of
        Jehonadab, our ancestor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[0]] of Babylon attacked this
        country, we were afraid of the Babylonian and Syrian[COMMENT[1]] armies.
        So we decided to move to Jerusalem. That is why we are here.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '35:11a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
          body: 
      - number: '35:11b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldean and Aramean.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: Go and say to the people in Judah and Jerusalem,
        \u2018Come and learn a lesson about how to obey me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Recabites do not drink wine to this day because their ancestor
        Jehonadab told them not to. But I have spoken to you again and again, and
        you refuse to obey me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Time after time I sent you prophets, who told you, \u201CTurn from
        your wicked ways, and start doing things right. Stop worshiping other gods
        so that you might live in peace here in the land I have given to you and
        your ancestors.\u201D But you would not listen to me or obey me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The descendants of Jehonadab son of Recab have obeyed their ancestor
        completely, but you have refused to listen to me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Because you refuse
        to listen or answer when I call, I will send upon Judah and Jerusalem all
        the disasters I have threatened.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jeremiah turned to the Recabites and said, \u201CThis is what
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel,
        says: \u2018You have obeyed your ancestor Jehonadab in every respect, following
        all his instructions.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Jehonadab son of Recab will always
        have descendants who serve me.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Messages"
      content: 'During the fourth year that Jehoiakim son of Josiah was king in Judah,[COMMENT[0]]
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments:
      - number: '36:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: "The fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign was 605 "
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGet a scroll, and write down all my messages against Israel,
        Judah, and the other nations. Begin with the first message back in the days
        of Josiah, and write down every message, right up to the present time. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Perhaps the people of Judah will repent when they hear again all
        the terrible things I have planned for them. Then I will be able to forgive
        their sins and wrongdoings.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Jeremiah sent for Baruch son of Neriah, and as Jeremiah dictated
        all the prophecies that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had given him, Baruch
        wrote them on a scroll. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Baruch, \u201CI am a prisoner here and unable
        to go to the Temple. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So you go to the Temple on the next day of fasting, and read the
        messages from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that I have had you write on
        this scroll. Read them so the people who are there from all over Judah will
        hear them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Perhaps even yet they will turn from their evil ways and ask the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s forgiveness before it is too late.
        For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has threatened them with his terrible
        anger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Baruch did as Jeremiah told him and read these messages from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to the people at the Temple. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He did this on a day of sacred fasting held in late autumn,[COMMENT[0]]
        during the fifth year of the reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah. People from
        all over Judah had come to Jerusalem to attend the services at the Temple
        on that day. '
      comments:
      - number: '36:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'in the ninth month, '
        - ft: "of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar (also in 36:22). The ninth month
            in the fifth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign occurred within the months
            of November and December 604 "
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Baruch read Jeremiah\u2019s words on the scroll to all the people.
        He stood in front of the Temple room of Gemariah, son of Shaphan the secretary.
        This room was just off the upper courtyard of the Temple, near the New Gate
        entrance.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Micaiah son of Gemariah and grandson of Shaphan heard the messages
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "he went down to the secretary\u2019s room in the palace where the
        administrative officials were meeting. Elishama the secretary was there,
        along with Delaiah son of Shemaiah, Elnathan son of Acbor, Gemariah son of
        Shaphan, Zedekiah son of Hananiah, and all the other officials. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Micaiah told them about the messages Baruch was reading to the
        people, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the officials sent Jehudi son of Nethaniah, grandson of Shelemiah
        and great-grandson of Cushi, to ask Baruch to come and read the messages
        to them, too. So Baruch took the scroll and went to them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSit down and read the scroll to us,\u201D the officials said,
        and Baruch did as they requested.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they heard all the messages, they looked at one another in alarm.
        \u201CWe must tell the king what we have heard,\u201D they said to Baruch. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut first, tell us how you got these messages. Did they come
        directly from Jeremiah?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Baruch explained, \u201CJeremiah dictated them, and I wrote them
        down in ink, word for word, on this scroll.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou and Jeremiah should both hide,\u201D the officials told
        Baruch. \u201CDon\u2019t tell anyone where you are!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the officials left the scroll for safekeeping in the room of
        Elishama the secretary and went to tell the king what had happened.  '
      comments: []
    - title: King Jehoiakim Burns the Scroll
      content: "The king sent Jehudi to get the scroll. Jehudi brought it from Elishama\u2019s
        room and read it to the king as all his officials stood by. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It was late autumn, and the king was in a winterized part of the
        palace, sitting in front of a fire to keep warm. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Each time Jehudi finished reading three or four columns, the king
        took a knife and cut off that section of the scroll. He then threw it into
        the fire, section by section, until the whole scroll was burned up. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Neither the king nor his attendants showed any signs of fear or repentance
        at what they heard. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even when Elnathan, Delaiah, and Gemariah begged the king not to
        burn the scroll, he wouldn\u2019t listen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the king commanded his son Jerahmeel, Seraiah son of Azriel,
        and Shelemiah son of Abdeel to arrest Baruch and Jeremiah. But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had hidden them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Jeremiah Rewrites the Scroll
      content: "After the king had burned the scroll on which Baruch had written
        Jeremiah\u2019s words, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Jeremiah another
        message. He said, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGet another scroll, and write everything again just as you
        did on the scroll King Jehoiakim burned. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then say to the king, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: You burned the scroll because it said the king of Babylon would destroy
        this land and empty it of people and animals. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about King
        Jehoiakim of Judah: He will have no heirs to sit on the throne of David.
        His dead body will be thrown out to lie unburied\u2014exposed to the heat
        of the day and the frost of the night. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will punish him and his family and his attendants for their sins.
        I will pour out on them and on all the people of Jerusalem and Judah all
        the disasters I promised, for they would not listen to my warnings.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: So Jeremiah took another scroll and dictated again to his secretary,
        Baruch. He wrote everything that had been on the scroll King Jehoiakim had
        burned in the fire. Only this time he added much more!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Zedekiah Calls for Jeremiah
      content: 'Zedekiah son of Josiah succeeded Jehoiachin[COMMENT[0]] son of Jehoiakim
        as the king of Judah. He was appointed by King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[1]]
        of Babylon. '
      comments:
      - number: '37:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Coniah, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
          body: 
      - number: '37:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'But neither King Zedekiah nor his attendants nor the people who were
        left in the land listened to what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said through
        Jeremiah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Nevertheless, King Zedekiah sent Jehucal son of Shelemiah, and Zephaniah
        the priest, son of Maaseiah, to ask Jeremiah, \u201CPlease pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jeremiah had not yet been imprisoned, so he could come and go among
        the people as he pleased.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At this time the army of Pharaoh Hophra[COMMENT[0]] of Egypt appeared
        at the southern border of Judah. When the Babylonian[COMMENT[1]] army heard
        about it, they withdrew from their siege of Jerusalem.  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:5a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'army of Pharaoh; '
        - ft: see 44:30.
          body: 
      - number: '37:5b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Chaldean; '
        - ft: also in 37:10, 11.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of
        Israel, says: The king of Judah sent you to ask me what is going to happen.
        Tell him, \u2018Pharaoh\u2019s army is about to return to Egypt, though he
        came here to help you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the Babylonians[COMMENT[0]] will come back and capture this
        city and burn it to the ground.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Chaldeans; '
        - ft: also in 37:9, 13.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Do not fool
        yourselves into thinking that the Babylonians are gone for good. They aren\u2019t! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even if you were to destroy the entire Babylonian army, leaving only
        a handful of wounded survivors, they would still stagger from their tents
        and burn this city to the ground!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jeremiah Is Imprisoned
      content: "When the Babylonian army left Jerusalem because of Pharaoh\u2019s
        approaching army, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jeremiah started to leave the city on his way to the territory of
        Benjamin, to claim his share of the property among his relatives there.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to separate from there in the midst of the people.
    - title: 
      content: "But as he was walking through the Benjamin Gate, a sentry arrested
        him and said, \u201CYou are defecting to the Babylonians!\u201D The sentry
        making the arrest was Irijah son of Shelemiah, grandson of Hananiah.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThat\u2019s not true!\u201D Jeremiah protested. \u201CI had
        no intention of doing any such thing.\u201D But Irijah wouldn\u2019t listen,
        and he took Jeremiah before the officials. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They were furious with Jeremiah and had him flogged and imprisoned
        in the house of Jonathan the secretary. Jonathan\u2019s house had been converted
        into a prison. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jeremiah was put into a dungeon cell, where he remained for many
        days.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Later King Zedekiah secretly requested that Jeremiah come to the
        palace, where the king asked him, \u201CDo you have any messages from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?\u201D\n\t\u201CYes, I do!\u201D said Jeremiah.
        \u201CYou will be defeated by the king of Babylon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jeremiah asked the king, \u201CWhat crime have I committed?
        What have I done against you, your attendants, or the people that I should
        be imprisoned like this? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Where are your prophets now who told you the king of Babylon would
        not attack you or this land? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen, my lord the king, I beg you. Don\u2019t send me back to the
        dungeon in the house of Jonathan the secretary, for I will die there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: So King Zedekiah commanded that Jeremiah not be returned to the dungeon.
        Instead, he was imprisoned in the courtyard of the guard in the royal palace.
        The king also commanded that Jeremiah be given a loaf of fresh bread every
        day as long as there was any left in the city. So Jeremiah was put in the
        palace prison.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jeremiah in a Cistern
      content: 'Now Shephatiah son of Mattan, Gedaliah son of Pashhur, Jehucal[COMMENT[0]]
        son of Shelemiah, and Pashhur son of Malkijah heard what Jeremiah had been
        telling the people. He had been saying, '
      comments:
      - number: '38:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jucal, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehucal; see 37:3.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018Everyone
        who stays in Jerusalem will die from war, famine, or disease, but those who
        surrender to the Babylonians[COMMENT[0]] will live. Their reward will be
        life. They will live!\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '38:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Chaldeans; '
        - ft: also in 38:18, 19, 23.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> also says: \u2018The city of Jerusalem
        will certainly be handed over to the army of the king of Babylon, who will
        capture it.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So these officials went to the king and said, \u201CSir, this man
        must die! That kind of talk will undermine the morale of the few fighting
        men we have left, as well as that of all the people. This man is a traitor!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "King Zedekiah agreed. \u201CAll right,\u201D he said. \u201CDo as
        you like. I can\u2019t stop you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the officials took Jeremiah from his cell and lowered him by ropes
        into an empty cistern in the prison yard. It belonged to Malkijah, a member
        of the royal family. There was no water in the cistern, but there was a thick
        layer of mud at the bottom, and Jeremiah sank down into it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But Ebed-melech the Ethiopian,[COMMENT[0]] an important court official,
        heard that Jeremiah was in the cistern. At that time the king was holding
        court at the Benjamin Gate, '
      comments:
      - number: '38:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Cushite.
    - title: 
      content: 'so Ebed-melech rushed from the palace to speak with him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy lord the king,\u201D he said, \u201Cthese men have done
        a very evil thing in putting Jeremiah the prophet into the cistern. He will
        soon die of hunger, for almost all the bread in the city is gone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So the king told Ebed-melech, \u201CTake thirty of my men with you,
        and pull Jeremiah out of the cistern before he dies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Ebed-melech took the men with him and went to a room in the palace
        beneath the treasury, where he found some old rags and discarded clothing.
        He carried these to the cistern and lowered them to Jeremiah on a rope. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ebed-melech called down to Jeremiah, \u201CPut these rags under your
        armpits to protect you from the ropes.\u201D Then when Jeremiah was ready, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "they pulled him out. So Jeremiah was returned to the courtyard of
        the guard\u2014the palace prison\u2014where he remained.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Zedekiah Questions Jeremiah
      content: "One day King Zedekiah sent for Jeremiah and had him brought to the
        third entrance of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Temple. \u201CI
        want to ask you something,\u201D the king said. \u201CAnd don\u2019t try
        to hide the truth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jeremiah said, \u201CIf I tell you the truth, you will kill me. And
        if I give you advice, you won\u2019t listen to me anyway.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So King Zedekiah secretly promised him, \u201CAs surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our Creator lives, I will not kill you or hand you over to the men who want
        you dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018If you surrender
        to the Babylonian officers, you and your family will live, and the city will
        not be burned down. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you refuse to surrender, you will not escape! This city will
        be handed over to the Babylonians, and they will burn it to the ground.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I am afraid to surrender,\u201D the king said, \u201Cfor
        the Babylonians may hand me over to the Judeans who have defected to them.
        And who knows what they will do to me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jeremiah replied, \u201CYou won\u2019t be handed over to them if
        you choose to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. Your life will be
        spared, and all will go well for you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if you refuse to surrender, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has revealed to me: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the women left in your palace will be brought out and given to
        the officers of the Babylonian army. Then the women will taunt you, saying,\n\t\u2018What
        fine friends you have!\n\tThey have betrayed and misled you.\n\tWhen your
        feet sank in the mud,\n\tthey left you to your fate!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All your wives and children will be led out to the Babylonians, and
        you will not escape. You will be seized by the king of Babylon, and this
        city will be burned down.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, \u201CDon\u2019t tell anyone you
        told me this, or you will die! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My officials may hear that I spoke to you, and they may say, \u2018Tell
        us what you and the king were talking about. If you don\u2019t tell us, we
        will kill you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If this happens, just tell them you begged me not to send you back
        to Jonathan\u2019s dungeon, for fear you would die there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Sure enough, it wasn\u2019t long before the king\u2019s officials
        came to Jeremiah and asked him why the king had called for him. But Jeremiah
        followed the king\u2019s instructions, and they left without finding out
        the truth. No one had overheard the conversation between Jeremiah and the
        king. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: And Jeremiah remained a prisoner in the courtyard of the guard until
        the day Jerusalem was captured.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      content: "In January[COMMENT[0]] of the ninth year of King Zedekiah\u2019s
        reign, King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[1]] of Babylon came with his entire army
        to besiege Jerusalem. "
      comments:
      - number: '39:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'In the tenth month, '
        - ft: 'of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar. A number of events in Jeremiah
            can be cross-checked with dates in surviving Babylonian records and related
            accurately to our modern calendar. This event occurred on January 15,
            588 '
          body: 
      - number: '39:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar; also in 39:5, 11.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Two and a half years later, on July 18[COMMENT[0]] in the eleventh
        year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign, a section of the city wall was broken down. "
      comments:
      - number: '39:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'On the ninth day of the fourth month. '
        - ft: 'This day was July 18, 586 '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "All the officers of the Babylonian army came in and sat in triumph
        at the Middle Gate: Nergal-sharezer of Samgar, and Nebo-sarsekim,[COMMENT[0]]
        a chief officer, and Nergal-sharezer, the king\u2019s adviser, and all the
        other officers of the king of Babylon.  "
      comments:
      - number: '39:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Nergal-sharezer, Samgar-nebo, Sarsekim.
    - title: 
      content: "When King Zedekiah of Judah and all the soldiers saw that the Babylonians
        had broken into the city, they fled. They waited for nightfall and then slipped
        through the gate between the two walls behind the king\u2019s garden and
        headed toward the Jordan Valley.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '39:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Arabah.
    - title: 
      content: 'But the Babylonian[COMMENT[0]] troops chased them and overtook Zedekiah
        on the plains of Jericho. They captured him and took him to King Nebuchadnezzar
        of Babylon, who was at Riblah in the land of Hamath. There the king of Babylon
        pronounced judgment upon Zedekiah. '
      comments:
      - number: '39:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Chaldean; '
        - ft: similarly in 39:8.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'The king of Babylon made Zedekiah watch as he slaughtered his sons
        at Riblah. The king of Babylon also slaughtered all the nobles of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he gouged out Zedekiah\u2019s eyes and bound him in bronze chains
        to lead him away to Babylon.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, the Babylonians burned Jerusalem, including the royal
        palace and the houses of the people, and they tore down the walls of the
        city. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, took as exiles to Babylon
        the rest of the people who remained in the city, those who had defected to
        him, and everyone else who remained. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But Nebuzaradan allowed some of the poorest people to stay behind
        in the land of Judah, and he assigned them to care for the vineyards and
        fields.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Jeremiah Remains in Judah
      content: 'King Nebuchadnezzar had told Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard,
        to find Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSee that he isn\u2019t hurt,\u201D he said. \u201CLook after
        him well, and give him anything he wants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard; Nebushazban, a chief officer;
        Nergal-sharezer, the king\u2019s adviser; and the other officers of Babylon\u2019s
        king "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'sent messengers to bring Jeremiah out of the prison. They put him
        under the care of Gedaliah son of Ahikam and grandson of Shaphan, who took
        him back to his home. So Jeremiah stayed in Judah among his own people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had given the following message to
        Jeremiah while he was still in prison: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSay to Ebed-melech the Ethiopian,[COMMENT[0]] \u2018This is
        what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of
        Israel, says: I will do to this city everything I have threatened. I will
        send disaster, not prosperity. You will see its destruction, "
      comments:
      - number: '39:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Cushite.
    - title: 
      content: 'but I will rescue you from those you fear so much. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Because you trusted me, I will give you your life as a reward. I
        will rescue you and keep you safe. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave a message to Jeremiah after
        Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, had released him at Ramah. He had
        found Jeremiah bound in chains among all the other captives of Jerusalem
        and Judah who were being sent to exile in Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The captain of the guard called for Jeremiah and said, \u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has brought this disaster on this land, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'just as he said he would. For these people have sinned against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and disobeyed him. That is why it happened. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I am going to take off your chains and let you go. If you want
        to come with me to Babylon, you are welcome. I will see that you are well
        cared for. But if you don\u2019t want to come, you may stay here. The whole
        land is before you\u2014go wherever you like. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you decide to stay, then return to Gedaliah son of Ahikam and
        grandson of Shaphan. He has been appointed governor of Judah by the king
        of Babylon. Stay there with the people he rules. But it\u2019s up to you;
        go wherever you like.\u201D\n\tThen Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard,
        gave Jeremiah some food and money and let him go. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Jeremiah returned to Gedaliah son of Ahikam at Mizpah, and he
        lived in Judah with the few who were still left in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Gedaliah Governs in Judah
      content: "The leaders of the Judean military groups in the countryside heard
        that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah son of Ahikam as governor
        over the poor people who were left behind in Judah\u2014the men, women, and
        children who hadn\u2019t been exiled to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they went to see Gedaliah at Mizpah. These included: Ishmael son
        of Nethaniah, Johanan and Jonathan sons of Kareah, Seraiah son of Tanhumeth,
        the sons of Ephai the Netophathite, Jezaniah son of the Maacathite, and all
        their men.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gedaliah vowed to them that the Babylonians[COMMENT[0]] meant them
        no harm. \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid to serve them. Live in the land and serve
        the king of Babylon, and all will go well for you,\u201D he promised. "
      comments:
      - number: '40:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Chaldeans; '
        - ft: also in 40:10.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs for me, I will stay at Mizpah to represent you before the
        Babylonians who come to meet with us. Settle in the towns you have taken,
        and live off the land. Harvest the grapes and summer fruits and olives, and
        store them away.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the Judeans in Moab, Ammon, Edom, and the other nearby countries
        heard that the king of Babylon had left a few people in Judah and that Gedaliah
        was the governor, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'they began to return to Judah from the places to which they had fled.
        They stopped at Mizpah to meet with Gedaliah and then went into the Judean
        countryside to gather a great harvest of grapes and other crops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: A Plot against Gedaliah
      content: 'Soon after this, Johanan son of Kareah and the other military leaders
        came to Gedaliah at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They said to him, \u201CDid you know that Baalis, king of Ammon,
        has sent Ishmael son of Nethaniah to assassinate you?\u201D But Gedaliah
        refused to believe them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Later Johanan had a private conference with Gedaliah and volunteered
        to kill Ishmael secretly. \u201CWhy should we let him come and murder you?\u201D
        Johanan asked. \u201CWhat will happen then to the Judeans who have returned?
        Why should the few of us who are still left be scattered and lost?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Gedaliah said to Johanan, \u201CI forbid you to do any such thing,
        for you are lying about Ishmael.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Murder of Gedaliah
      content: "But in midautumn of that year,[COMMENT[0]] Ishmael son of Nethaniah
        and grandson of Elishama, who was a member of the royal family and had been
        one of the king\u2019s high officials, went to Mizpah with ten men to meet
        Gedaliah. While they were eating together, "
      comments:
      - number: '41:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'in the seventh month, '
        - ft: 'of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar. This month occurred within the
            months of October and November 586 '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Ishmael and his ten men suddenly jumped up, drew their swords, and
        killed Gedaliah, whom the king of Babylon had appointed governor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Ishmael also killed all the Judeans and the Babylonian[COMMENT[0]]
        soldiers who were with Gedaliah at Mizpah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldean.
    - title: 
      content: "The next day, before anyone had heard about Gedaliah\u2019s murder, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "eighty men arrived from Shechem, Shiloh, and Samaria to worship at
        the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. They had shaved off their
        beards, torn their clothes, and cut themselves, and had brought along grain
        offerings and frankincense. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ishmael left Mizpah to meet them, weeping as he went. When he reached
        them, he said, \u201COh, come and see what has happened to Gedaliah!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But as soon as they were all inside the town, Ishmael and his men
        killed all but ten of them and threw their bodies into a cistern. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The other ten had talked Ishmael into letting them go by promising
        to bring him their stores of wheat, barley, olive oil, and honey that they
        had hidden away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The cistern where Ishmael dumped the bodies of the men he murdered
        was the large one[COMMENT[0]] dug by King Asa when he fortified Mizpah to
        protect himself against King Baasha of Israel. Ishmael son of Nethaniah filled
        it with corpses.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: murdered because of Gedaliah was one.
    - title: 
      content: "Then Ishmael made captives of the king\u2019s daughters and the other
        people who had been left under Gedaliah\u2019s care in Mizpah by Nebuzaradan,
        the captain of the guard. Taking them with him, he started back toward the
        land of Ammon.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when Johanan son of Kareah and the other military leaders heard
        about Ishmael\u2019s crimes, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'they took all their men and set out to stop him. They caught up with
        him at the large pool near Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people Ishmael had captured shouted for joy when they saw Johanan
        and the other military leaders. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And all the captives from Mizpah escaped and began to help Johanan. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, Ishmael and eight of his men escaped from Johanan into
        the land of Ammon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Johanan son of Kareah and the other military leaders took all
        the people they had rescued in Gibeon\u2014the soldiers, women, children,
        and court officials[COMMENT[0]] whom Ishmael had captured after he killed
        Gedaliah. "
      comments:
      - number: '41:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: eunuchs.
    - title: 
      content: 'They took them all to the village of Geruth-kimham near Bethlehem,
        where they prepared to leave for Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: They were afraid of what the Babylonians[COMMENT[0]] would do when
        they heard that Ishmael had killed Gedaliah, the governor appointed by the
        Babylonian king.
      comments:
      - number: '41:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldeans.
  - verses:
    - title: Warning to Stay in Judah
      content: 'Then all the military leaders, including Johanan son of Kareah and
        Jezaniah[COMMENT[0]] son of Hoshaiah, and all the people, from the least
        to the greatest, approached '
      comments:
      - number: '42:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'Azariah; '
        - ft: compare 43:2.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Jeremiah the prophet. They said, \u201CPlease pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God for us. As you can see, we are only a tiny remnant compared to what
        we were before. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pray that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will show us what
        to do and where to go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll right,\u201D Jeremiah replied. \u201CI will pray to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, as you have asked, and I will tell
        you everything he says. I will hide nothing from you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they said to Jeremiah, \u201CMay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God be a faithful witness against us if we refuse to obey whatever he
        tells us to do! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Whether we like it or not, we will obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God to whom we are sending you with our plea. For if we obey him, everything
        will turn out well for us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Ten days later the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave his reply to
        Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So he called for Johanan son of Kareah and the other military leaders,
        and for all the people, from the least to the greatest. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said to them, \u201CYou sent me to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of Israel, with your request, and this is his reply: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Stay here in this land. If you do, I will build you up and
        not tear you down; I will plant you and not uproot you. For I am sorry about
        all the punishment I have had to bring upon you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not fear the king of Babylon anymore,\u2019 says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        \u2018For I am with you and will save you and rescue you from his power. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will be merciful to you by making him kind, so he will let you
        stay here in your land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if you refuse to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, and if you say, \u2018We will not stay here; "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "instead, we will go to Egypt where we will be free from war, the
        call to arms, and hunger,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then hear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s message to the
        remnant of Judah. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018If you are determined to go to Egypt
        and live there, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the very war and famine you fear will catch up to you, and you will
        die there. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is the fate awaiting every one of you who insists on going to
        live in Egypt. Yes, you will die from war, famine, and disease. None of you
        will escape the disaster I will bring upon you there.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Just as my anger and fury have been
        poured out on the people of Jerusalem, so they will be poured out on you
        when you enter Egypt. You will be an object of damnation, horror, cursing,
        and mockery. And you will never see your homeland again.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen, you remnant of Judah. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has told you: \u2018Do not go to Egypt!\u2019 Don\u2019t forget this warning
        I have given you today. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For you were not being honest when you sent me to pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God for you. You said, \u2018Just tell us what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God says, and we will do it!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And today I have told you exactly what he said, but you will not
        obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God any better now than you have
        in the past. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So you can be sure that you will die from war, famine, and disease
        in Egypt, where you insist on going.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jeremiah Taken to Egypt
      content: 'When Jeremiah had finished giving this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God to all the people, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Azariah son of Hoshaiah and Johanan son of Kareah and all the other
        proud men said to Jeremiah, \u201CYou lie! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God hasn\u2019t forbidden us to go to Egypt! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Baruch son of Neriah has convinced you to say this, because he wants
        us to stay here and be killed by the Babylonians[COMMENT[0]] or be carried
        off into exile.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '43:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldeans.
    - title: 
      content: "So Johanan and the other military leaders and all the people refused
        to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s command to stay in Judah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Johanan and the other leaders took with them all the people who had
        returned from the nearby countries to which they had fled. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the crowd were men, women, and children, the king\u2019s daughters,
        and all those whom Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, had left with Gedaliah.
        The prophet Jeremiah and Baruch were also included. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people refused to obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and went to Egypt, going as far as the city of Tahpanhes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then at Tahpanhes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message
        to Jeremiah. He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhile the people of Judah are watching, take some large rocks
        and bury them under the pavement stones at the entrance of Pharaoh\u2019s
        palace here in Tahpanhes. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then say to the people of Judah, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: I will certainly bring
        my servant Nebuchadnezzar,[COMMENT[0]] king of Babylon, here to Egypt. I
        will set his throne over these stones that I have hidden. He will spread
        his royal canopy over them. "
      comments:
      - number: '43:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'And when he comes, he will destroy the land of Egypt. He will bring
        death to those destined for death, captivity to those destined for captivity,
        and war to those destined for war. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will set fire to the temples of Egypt\u2019s gods; he will burn
        the temples and carry the idols away as plunder. He will pick clean the land
        of Egypt as a shepherd picks fleas from his cloak. And he himself will leave
        unharmed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will break down the sacred pillars standing in the temple of the
        sun[COMMENT[0]] in Egypt, and he will burn down the temples of Egypt\u2019s
        gods.\u2019\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '43:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: in Heliopolis.
  - verses:
    - title: Judgment for Idolatry
      content: 'This is the message Jeremiah received concerning the Judeans living
        in northern Egypt in the cities of Migdol, Tahpanhes, and Memphis,[COMMENT[0]]
        and in southern Egypt[COMMENT[1]] as well: '
      comments:
      - number: '44:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Noph.
      - number: '44:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: in Pathros.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: You saw the calamity I brought on Jerusalem
        and all the towns of Judah. They now lie deserted and in ruins. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They provoked my anger with all their wickedness. They burned incense
        and worshiped other gods\u2014gods that neither they nor you nor any of your
        ancestors had ever even known.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAgain and again I sent my servants, the prophets, to plead
        with them, \u2018Don\u2019t do these horrible things that I hate so much.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But my people would not listen or turn back from their wicked ways.
        They kept on burning incense to these gods. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And so my fury boiled over and fell like fire on the towns of Judah
        and into the streets of Jerusalem, and they are still a desolate ruin today.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, asks you: Why are you destroying yourselves? For
        not one of you will survive\u2014not a man, woman, or child among you who
        has come here from Judah, not even the babies in your arms. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why provoke my anger by burning incense to the idols you have made
        here in Egypt? You will only destroy yourselves and make yourselves an object
        of cursing and mockery for all the nations of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have you forgotten the sins of your ancestors, the sins of the kings
        and queens of Judah, and the sins you and your wives committed in Judah and
        Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To this very hour you have shown no remorse or reverence. No one
        has chosen to follow my word and the decrees I gave to you and your ancestors
        before you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: I am determined to destroy
        every one of you! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will take this remnant of Judah\u2014those who were determined
        to come here and live in Egypt\u2014and I will consume them. They will fall
        here in Egypt, killed by war and famine. All will die, from the least to
        the greatest. They will be an object of damnation, horror, cursing, and mockery. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will punish them in Egypt just as I punished them in Jerusalem,
        by war, famine, and disease. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Of that remnant who fled to Egypt, hoping someday to return to Judah,
        there will be no survivors. Even though they long to return home, only a
        handful will do so.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then all the women present and all the men who knew that their wives
        had burned incense to idols\u2014a great crowd of all the Judeans living
        in northern Egypt and southern Egypt[COMMENT[0]]\u2014answered Jeremiah, "
      comments:
      - number: '44:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: in Egypt, in Pathros.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWe will not listen to your messages from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We will do whatever we want. We will burn incense and pour out liquid
        offerings to the Queen of Heaven just as much as we like\u2014just as we,
        and our ancestors, and our kings and officials have always done in the towns
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem. For in those days we had plenty
        to eat, and we were well off and had no troubles! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But ever since we quit burning incense to the Queen of Heaven and
        stopped worshiping her with liquid offerings, we have been in great trouble
        and have been dying from war and famine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBesides,\u201D the women added, \u201Cdo you suppose that we
        were burning incense and pouring out liquid offerings to the Queen of Heaven,
        and making cakes marked with her image, without our husbands knowing it and
        helping us? Of course not!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jeremiah said to all of them, men and women alike, who had given
        him that answer, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo you think the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did not know that
        you and your ancestors, your kings and officials, and all the people were
        burning incense to idols in the towns of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It was because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> could no longer bear
        all the disgusting things you were doing that he made your land an object
        of cursing\u2014a desolate ruin without inhabitants\u2014as it is today. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All these terrible things happened to you because you have burned
        incense to idols and sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        You have refused to obey him and have not followed his instructions, his
        decrees, and his laws.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to them all, including the women, \u201CListen
        to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, all you citizens
        of Judah who live in Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u2018You and your wives have said, \u201CWe will
        keep our promises to burn incense and pour out liquid offerings to the Queen
        of Heaven,\u201D and you have proved by your actions that you meant it. So
        go ahead and carry out your promises and vows to her!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        all you Judeans now living in Egypt: \u2018I have sworn by my great name,\u2019
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, \u2018that my name will no longer
        be spoken by any of the Judeans in the land of Egypt. None of you may invoke
        my name or use this oath: \u201CAs surely as the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I will watch over you to bring you disaster and not good. Everyone
        from Judah who is now living in Egypt will suffer war and famine until all
        of you are dead. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Only a small number will escape death and return to Judah from Egypt.
        Then all those who came to Egypt will find out whose words are true\u2014mine
        or theirs!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018And this is the proof I give you,\u2019 says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u2018that all I have threatened will happen to you and that I will punish
        you here.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018I will turn
        Pharaoh Hophra, king of Egypt, over to his enemies who want to kill him,
        just as I turned King Zedekiah of Judah over to King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[0]]
        of Babylon.\u2019\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '44:30 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
          body: 
  - verses:
    - title: A Message for Baruch
      content: 'The prophet Jeremiah gave a message to Baruch son of Neriah in the
        fourth year of the reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah,[COMMENT[0]] after Baruch
        had written down everything Jeremiah had dictated to him. He said, '
      comments:
      - number: '45:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: "The fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign was 605 "
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of
        Israel, says to you, Baruch: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have said, \u2018I am overwhelmed with trouble! Haven\u2019t
        I had enough pain already? And now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has added
        more! I am worn out from sighing and can find no rest.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBaruch, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        \u2018I will destroy this nation that I built. I will uproot what I planted. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are you seeking great things for yourself? Don\u2019t do it! I will
        bring great disaster upon all these people; but I will give you your life
        as a reward wherever you go. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have
        spoken!\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Messages for the Nations
      content: 'The following messages were given to Jeremiah the prophet from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning foreign nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Messages about Egypt
      content: 'This message concerning Egypt was given in the fourth year of the
        reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah, the king of Judah, on the occasion of the
        battle of Carchemish[COMMENT[0]] when Pharaoh Neco, king of Egypt, and his
        army were defeated beside the Euphrates River by King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[1]]
        of Babylon.  '
      comments:
      - number: '46:2a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'This event occurred in 605 '
          body: 
      - number: '46:2b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar; also in 46:13, 26.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPrepare your shields,\n\tand advance into battle!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Harness the horses,\n\tand mount the stallions.\n\tTake your positions.\n\tPut
        on your helmets.\n\tSharpen your spears,\n\tand prepare your armor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But what do I see?\n\tThe Egyptian army flees in terror.\n\tThe bravest
        of its fighting men run\n\twithout a backward glance.\n\tThey are terrorized
        at every turn,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe swiftest runners cannot flee;\n\tthe mightiest warriors
        cannot escape.\n\tBy the Euphrates River to the north,\n\tthey stumble and
        fall.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho is this, rising like the Nile at floodtime,\n\toverflowing
        all the land?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is the Egyptian army,\n\toverflowing all the land,\n\tboasting
        that it will cover the earth like a flood,\n\tdestroying cities and their
        people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Charge, you horses and chariots;\n\tattack, you mighty warriors of
        Egypt!\n\tCome, all you allies from Ethiopia, Libya, and Lydia[COMMENT[0]]who
        are skilled with the shield and bow!  "
      comments:
      - number: '46:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: from Cush, Put, and Lud.
    - title: 
      content: "For this is the day of the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies,\n\ta day of vengeance on his enemies.\n\tThe sword
        will devour until it is satisfied,\n\tyes, until it is drunk with your blood!\n\tThe
        Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, will receive
        a sacrifice today\n\tin the north country beside the Euphrates River.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo up to Gilead to get medicine,\n\tO virgin daughter of Egypt!\n\tBut
        your many treatments\n\twill bring you no healing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The nations have heard of your shame.\n\tThe earth is filled with
        your cries of despair.\n\tYour mightiest warriors will run into each other\n\tand
        fall down together.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave the prophet Jeremiah this
        message about King Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s plans to attack Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CShout it out in Egypt!\n\tPublish it in the cities of Migdol,
        Memphis,[COMMENT[0]] and Tahpanhes!\n\tMobilize for battle,\n\tfor the sword
        will devour everyone around you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '46:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Noph; '
        - ft: also in 46:19.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Why have your warriors fallen?\n\tThey cannot stand, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has knocked them down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They stumble and fall over each other\n\tand say among themselves,\n\t\u2018Come,
        let\u2019s go back to our people,\n\tto the land of our birth.\n\tLet\u2019s
        get away from the sword of the enemy!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There they will say,\n\t\u2018Pharaoh, the king of Egypt, is a loudmouth\n\twho
        missed his opportunity!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs surely as I live,\u201D says the King,\n\twhose name is
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,\n\t\u201Cone is
        coming against Egypt\n\twho is as tall as Mount Tabor,\n\tor as Mount Carmel
        by the sea!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pack up! Get ready to leave for exile,\n\tyou citizens of Egypt!\n\tThe
        city of Memphis will be destroyed,\n\twithout a single inhabitant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Egypt is as sleek as a beautiful heifer,\n\tbut a horsefly from the
        north is on its way!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Egypt\u2019s mercenaries have become like fattened calves.\n\tThey,
        too, will turn and run,\n\tfor it is a day of great disaster for Egypt,\n\ta
        time of great punishment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Egypt flees, silent as a serpent gliding away.\n\tThe invading army
        marches in;\n\tthey come against her with axes like woodsmen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will cut down her people like trees,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cfor
        they are more numerous than locusts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Egypt will be humiliated;\n\tshe will be handed over to people from
        the north.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God
        of Israel, says: \u201CI will punish Amon, the god of Thebes,[COMMENT[0]]
        and all the other gods of Egypt. I will punish its rulers and Pharaoh, too,
        and all who trust in him. "
      comments:
      - number: '46:25 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: of No.
    - title: 
      content: "I will hand them over to those who want them killed\u2014to King
        Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon and his army. But afterward the land will recover
        from the ravages of war. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut do not be afraid, Jacob, my servant;\n\tdo not be dismayed,
        Israel.\n\tFor I will bring you home again from distant lands,\n\tand your
        children will return from their exile.\n\tIsrael[COMMENT[0]] will return
        to a life of peace and quiet,\n\tand no one will terrorize them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '46:27 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jacob. '
        - ft: See note on 5:20.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Do not be afraid, Jacob, my servant,\n\tfor I am with you,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CI will completely destroy
        the nations to which I have exiled you,\n\tbut I will not completely destroy
        you.\n\tI will discipline you, but with justice;\n\tI cannot let you go unpunished.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Philistia
      content: "This is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s message to the
        prophet Jeremiah concerning the Philistines of Gaza, before it was captured
        by the Egyptian army. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CA flood
        is coming from the north\n\tto overflow the land.\n\tIt will destroy the
        land and everything in it\u2014\n\tcities and people alike.\n\tPeople will
        scream in terror,\n\tand everyone in the land will wail.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hear the clatter of stallions\u2019 hooves\n\tand the rumble of wheels
        as the chariots rush by.\n\tTerrified fathers run madly,\n\twithout a backward
        glance at their helpless children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe time has come for the Philistines to be destroyed,\n\talong
        with their allies from Tyre and Sidon.\n\tYes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is destroying the remnant of the Philistines,\n\tthose colonists from the
        island of Crete.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '47:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: from Caphtor.
    - title: 
      content: "Gaza will be humiliated, its head shaved bald;\n\tAshkelon will lie
        silent.\n\tYou remnant from the Mediterranean coast,[COMMENT[0]]how long
        will you cut yourselves in mourning?  "
      comments:
      - number: '47:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the plain.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow, O sword of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\twhen
        will you be at rest again?\n\tGo back into your sheath;\n\trest and be still.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut how can it be still\n\twhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has sent it on a mission?\n\tFor the city of Ashkelon\n\tand the people living
        along the sea\n\tmust be destroyed.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Moab
      content: "This message was given concerning Moab. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says:\n\t\u201CWhat sorrow awaits
        the city of Nebo;\n\tit will soon lie in ruins.\n\tThe city of Kiriathaim
        will be humiliated and captured;\n\tthe fortress will be humiliated and broken
        down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one will ever brag about Moab again,\n\tfor in Heshbon there is
        a plot to destroy her.\n\t\u2018Come,\u2019 they say, \u2018we will cut her
        off from being a nation.\u2019\n\tThe town of Madmen,[COMMENT[0]] too, will
        be silenced;\n\tthe sword will follow you there.  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Madmen '
        - ft: "sounds like the Hebrew word for \u201Csilence\u201D; it should not
            be confused with the English word "
          body: madmen.
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to the cries from Horonaim,\n\tcries of devastation and great
        destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All Moab is destroyed.\n\tHer little ones will cry out.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: Her cries are heard as far away as Zoar.
    - title: 
      content: "Her refugees weep bitterly,\n\tclimbing the slope to Luhith.\n\tThey
        cry out in terror,\n\tdescending the slope to Horonaim.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Flee for your lives!\n\tHide[COMMENT[0]] in the wilderness!  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Hide like a wild donkey; '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: 'Hide like a juniper shrub; '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: 'Be like '
        - ft: '[the town of] '
          body: 'Aroer. '
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Because you have trusted in your wealth and skill,\n\tyou will be
        taken captive.\n\tYour god Chemosh, with his priests and officials,\n\twill
        be hauled off to distant lands!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll the towns will be destroyed,\n\tand no one will escape\u2014\n\teither
        on the plateaus or in the valleys,\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, that Moab had wings\n\tso she could fly away,[COMMENT[0]]for
        her towns will be left empty,\n\twith no one living in them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Put salt on Moab, / for she will be laid waste.
    - title: 
      content: "Cursed are those who refuse to do the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        work,\n\twho hold back their swords from shedding blood!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFrom his earliest history, Moab has lived in peace,\n\tnever
        going into exile.\n\tHe is like wine that has been allowed to settle.\n\tHe
        has not been poured from flask to flask,\n\tand he is now fragrant and smooth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the time is coming soon,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cwhen
        I will send men to pour him from his jar.\n\tThey will pour him out,\n\tthen
        shatter the jar!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At last Moab will be ashamed of his idol Chemosh,\n\tas the people
        of Israel were ashamed of their gold calf at Bethel.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: ashamed when they trusted in Bethel.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou used to boast, \u2018We are heroes,\n\tmighty men of war.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now Moab and his towns will be destroyed.\n\tHis most promising
        youth are doomed to slaughter,\u201D\n\tsays the King, whose name is the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDestruction is coming fast for Moab;\n\tcalamity threatens
        ominously.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You friends of Moab,\n\tweep for him and cry!\n\tSee how the strong
        scepter is broken,\n\thow the beautiful staff is shattered!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome down from your glory\n\tand sit in the dust, you people
        of Dibon,\n\tfor those who destroy Moab will shatter Dibon, too.\n\tThey
        will tear down all your towers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You people of Aroer,\n\tstand beside the road and watch.\n\tShout
        to those who flee from Moab,\n\t\u2018What has happened there?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd the reply comes back,\n\t\u2018Moab lies in ruins, disgraced;\n\tweep
        and wail!\n\tTell it by the banks of the Arnon River:\n\tMoab has been destroyed!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Judgment has been poured out on the towns of the plateau\u2014\n\ton
        Holon and Jahaz[COMMENT[0]] and Mephaath,  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jahzah, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jahaz.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'on Dibon and Nebo and Beth-diblathaim,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'on Kiriathaim and Beth-gamul and Beth-meon,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "on Kerioth and Bozrah\u2014\n\tall the towns of Moab, far and near.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe strength of Moab has ended.\n\tHis arm has been broken,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLet him stagger and fall like a drunkard,\n\tfor he has rebelled
        against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tMoab will wallow in his own
        vomit,\n\tridiculed by all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Did you not ridicule the people of Israel?\n\tWere they caught in
        the company of thieves\n\tthat you should despise them as you do?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou people of Moab,\n\tflee from your towns and live in the
        caves.\n\tHide like doves that nest\n\tin the clefts of the rocks.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We have all heard of the pride of Moab,\n\tfor his pride is very
        great.\n\tWe know of his lofty pride,\n\this arrogance, and his haughty heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I know about his insolence,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cbut
        his boasts are empty\u2014\n\tas empty as his deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now I wail for Moab;\n\tyes, I will mourn for Moab.\n\tMy heart
        is broken for the men of Kir-hareseth.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:31 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Kir-heres, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Kir-hareseth; also in 48:36.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou people of Sibmah, rich in vineyards,\n\tI will weep for
        you even more than I did for Jazer.\n\tYour spreading vines once reached
        as far as the Dead Sea,[COMMENT[0]]but the destroyer has stripped you bare!\n\tHe
        has harvested your grapes and summer fruits.  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:32 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the sea of Jazer.
    - title: 
      content: "Joy and gladness are gone from fruitful Moab.\n\tThe presses yield
        no wine.\n\tNo one treads the grapes with shouts of joy.\n\tThere is shouting,
        yes, but not of joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CInstead, their awful cries of terror can be heard from Heshbon
        clear across to Elealeh and Jahaz; from Zoar all the way to Horonaim and
        Eglath-shelishiyah. Even the waters of Nimrim are dried up now.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will put an end to Moab,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cfor the people offer sacrifices at the pagan shrines and burn incense
        to their false gods. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My heart moans like a flute for Moab and Kir-hareseth, for all their
        wealth has disappeared. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people shave their heads and beards in mourning. They slash their
        hands and put on clothes made of burlap. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There is crying and sorrow in every Moabite home and on every street.
        For I have smashed Moab like an old, unwanted jar. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How it is shattered! Hear the wailing! See the shame of Moab! It
        has become an object of ridicule, an example of ruin to all its neighbors.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CLook!
        The enemy swoops down like an eagle,\n\tspreading his wings over Moab.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Its cities will fall,\n\tand its strongholds will be seized.\n\tEven
        the mightiest warriors will be in anguish\n\tlike a woman in labor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moab will no longer be a nation,\n\tfor it has boasted against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTerror and traps and snares will be your lot,\n\tO Moab,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThose who flee in terror will fall into a trap,\n\tand those
        who escape the trap will step into a snare.\n\tI will see to it that you
        do not get away,\n\tfor the time of your judgment has come,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe people flee as far as Heshbon\n\tbut are unable to go on.\n\tFor
        a fire comes from Heshbon,\n\tKing Sihon\u2019s ancient home,\n\tto devour
        the entire land\n\twith all its rebellious people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you, O people of Moab!\n\tThe people of
        the god Chemosh are destroyed!\n\tYour sons and your daughters\n\thave been
        taken away as captives.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will restore the fortunes of Moab\n\tin days to come.\n\tI,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D\n\tThis is the end
        of Jeremiah\u2019s prophecy concerning Moab."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Ammon
      content: "This message was given concerning the Ammonites. This is what the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CAre there no descendants of Israel\n\tto
        inherit the land of Gad?\n\tWhy are you, who worship Molech,[COMMENT[0]]living
        in its towns?  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Malcam, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Molech; also in 49:3.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "In the days to come,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201CI
        will sound the battle cry against your city of Rabbah.\n\tIt will become
        a desolate heap of ruins,\n\tand the neighboring towns will be burned.\n\tThen
        Israel will take back the land\n\tyou took from her,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCry out, O Heshbon,\n\tfor the town of Ai is destroyed.\n\tWeep,
        O people of Rabbah!\n\tPut on your clothes of mourning.\n\tWeep and wail,
        hiding in the hedges,\n\tfor your god Molech, with his priests and officials,\n\twill
        be hauled off to distant lands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You are proud of your fertile valleys,\n\tbut they will soon be ruined.\n\tYou
        trusted in your wealth,\n\tyou rebellious daughter,\n\tand thought no one
        could ever harm you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But look! I will bring terror upon you,\u201D\n\tsays the Lord, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\n\t\u201CYour neighbors
        will chase you from your land,\n\tand no one will help your exiles as they
        flee.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will restore the fortunes of the Ammonites\n\tin days to come.\n\tI,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Messages about Edom
      content: "This message was given concerning Edom. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says:\n\t\u201CIs there no wisdom in Teman?\n\tIs
        no one left to give wise counsel?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Turn and flee!\n\tHide in deep caves, you people of Dedan!\n\tFor
        when I bring disaster on Edom,[COMMENT[0]]I will punish you, too!  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Esau; '
        - ft: also in 49:10.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Those who harvest grapes\n\talways leave a few for the poor.\n\tIf
        thieves came at night,\n\tthey would not take everything.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will strip bare the land of Edom,\n\tand there will be no place
        left to hide.\n\tIts children, its brothers, and its neighbors\n\twill all
        be destroyed,\n\tand Edom itself will be no more.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will protect the orphans who remain among you.\n\tYour widows,
        too, can depend on me for help.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CIf the
        innocent must suffer, how much more must you! You will not go unpunished!
        You must drink this cup of judgment! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I have sworn by my own name,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201Cthat Bozrah will become an object of horror and a heap of ruins; it
        will be mocked and cursed. All its towns and villages will be desolate forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have heard a message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tthat
        an ambassador was sent to the nations to say,\n\t\u201CForm a coalition against
        Edom,\n\tand prepare for battle!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to Edom,\n\t\u201CI will cut
        you down to size among the nations.\n\tYou will be despised by all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have been deceived\n\tby the fear you inspire in others\n\tand
        by your own pride.\n\tYou live in a rock fortress\n\tand control the mountain
        heights.\n\tBut even if you make your nest among the peaks with the eagles,\n\tI
        will bring you crashing down,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEdom will be an object of horror.\n\tAll who pass by will be
        appalled\n\tand will gasp at the destruction they see there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It will be like the destruction of Sodom and Gomorrah\n\tand their
        neighboring towns,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CNo
        one will live there;\n\tno one will inhabit it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will come like a lion from the thickets of the Jordan,\n\tleaping
        on the sheep in the pasture.\n\tI will chase Edom from its land,\n\tand I
        will appoint the leader of my choice.\n\tFor who is like me, and who can
        challenge me?\n\tWhat ruler can oppose my will?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s plans against
        Edom\n\tand the people of Teman.\n\tEven the little children will be dragged
        off like sheep,\n\tand their homes will be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth will shake with the noise of Edom\u2019s fall,\n\tand its
        cry of despair will be heard all the way to the Red Sea.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: sea of reeds.
    - title: 
      content: "Look! The enemy swoops down like an eagle,\n\tspreading his wings
        over Bozrah.\n\tEven the mightiest warriors will be in anguish\n\tlike a
        woman in labor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Damascus
      content: "This message was given concerning Damascus. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\n\t\u201CThe towns of Hamath and Arpad are struck with fear,\n\tfor
        they have heard the news of their destruction.\n\tTheir hearts are troubled\n\tlike
        a wild sea in a raging storm.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Damascus has become feeble,\n\tand all her people turn to flee.\n\tFear,
        anguish, and pain have gripped her\n\tas they grip a woman in labor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That famous city, a city of joy,\n\twill be forsaken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Her young men will fall in the streets and die.\n\tHer soldiers will
        all be killed,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd I will set fire to the walls of Damascus\n\tthat will burn
        up the palaces of Ben-hadad.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Kedar and Hazor
      content: "This message was given concerning Kedar and the kingdoms of Hazor,
        which were attacked by King Nebuchadnezzar[COMMENT[0]] of Babylon. This is
        what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CAdvance against Kedar!\n\tDestroy
        the warriors from the East!  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:28 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Nebuchadrezzar, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar; also in 49:30.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Their flocks and tents will be captured,\n\tand their household goods
        and camels will be taken away.\n\tEverywhere shouts of panic will be heard:\n\t\u2018We
        are terrorized at every turn!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Run for your lives,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CHide
        yourselves in deep caves, you people of Hazor,\n\tfor King Nebuchadnezzar
        of Babylon has plotted against you\n\tand is preparing to destroy you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo up and attack that complacent nation,\u201D\n\tsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CIts people live alone in the desert\n\twithout
        walls or gates.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their camels and other livestock will all be yours.\n\tI will scatter
        to the winds these people\n\twho live in remote places.[COMMENT[0]]I will
        bring calamity upon them\n\tfrom every direction,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:32 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: who clip the corners of their hair.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHazor will be inhabited by jackals,\n\tand it will be desolate
        forever.\n\tNo one will live there;\n\tno one will inhabit it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Elam
      content: 'This message concerning Elam came to the prophet Jeremiah from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at the beginning of the reign of King Zedekiah
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\n\t\u201CI will destroy the archers of Elam\u2014\n\tthe best of their
        forces.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will bring enemies from all directions,\n\tand I will scatter the
        people of Elam to the four winds.\n\tThey will be exiled to countries around
        the world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I myself will go with Elam\u2019s enemies to shatter it.\n\tIn my
        fierce anger, I will bring great disaster\n\tupon the people of Elam,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CTheir enemies will chase
        them with the sword\n\tuntil I have destroyed them completely.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will set my throne in Elam,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cand
        I will destroy its king and officials.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will restore the fortunes of Elam\n\tin days to come.\n\tI,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Babylon
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Jeremiah the prophet this message
