    - title: "Hope for Israel\u2019s Royal Line"
      content: 'In the thirty-seventh year of the exile of King Jehoiachin of Judah,
        Evil-merodach ascended to the Babylonian throne. He was kind to[COMMENT[0]]
        Jehoiachin and released him from prison on March 31 of that year.[COMMENT[1]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '52:31a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: He raised the head of.
      - number: '52:31b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'on the twenty-fifth day of the twelfth month, '
        - ft: 'of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar. This day was March 31, 561 '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'He spoke kindly to Jehoiachin and gave him a higher place than all
        the other exiled kings in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He supplied Jehoiachin with new clothes to replace his prison garb
        and allowed him to dine in the king\u2019s presence for the rest of his life. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: So the Babylonian king gave him a regular food allowance as long as
        he lived. This continued until the day of his death.
